   <p><li> Michael A. Dornheim and David Hughes, "U.S. Intensifies Efforts to Meet Missile Threat," <I>Aviation Week and Space Technology</I>, October 16, 1995, p. 36; the necessity for U.S. F-15 pilots to close in on targets due to identification requirements during the Gulf War is illustrated in Paul Crickmore, "Star of the Storm," <I>Air International</I>, January 1992, p. 17.
 <p><li>   Hughes, "Russians Offer AA-11s to McDonnell Douglas."
   <p><li> Steven Zaloga, "Harpoonski," <I>U.S. Naval Institute Proceedings</I>, February 1994, p. 38.
