<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Indexicon Spec Sheet</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="ABOOK.GIF" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" link="#0000FF" vlink="#663399">

<table width=600><tr>

<td width=150 align=left valign=top>
<a href="../INDEX.HTM"><img src="INDXHOME.GIF" border=0 alt="Indexicon HomePage"></A><BR>
<a href="SPECSHT.HTM"><img src="DESCRIP.GIF" border=0 alt="Description"></A><BR>
<a href="../DOMINION/INDEX_1.HTM"><img src="DEMO.GIF" border=0 alt="Download Demo"></A><BR>
<a href="REVIEWS.HTM"><img src="REVIEWS.GIF" border=0 alt="Reviews"></A><BR>
<a href="DEMOS.HTM"><img src="DEMOS.GIF" border=0 alt="Demonstrations"></A><BR>
<a href="ORDER.HTM"><img src="ORDER.GIF" border=0 alt="Order"></A><BR>
<a href="INDXFAQ.HTM"><img src="FAQ.GIF" border=0 alt="FAQ"></A><BR>
<a href="SPECSHT.HTM#sysreq"><img src="REQUIRE.GIF" border=0 alt="System Requirements"></A><BR>
<a href="TECHSUPP.HTM"><img src="SUPPORT.GIF" border=0 alt="Support"></A><BR>
<a href="../HOMEPAGE.HTM"><img src="ICVXHOME.GIF" border=0 alt="Iconovex HomePage"></A></td>

<td valign=top width=450>
<center>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="INDXCN1.GIF" ALT="Indexicon Logo">
<BR><B><font size=+2 face=arial>Product Description<BR>System
Requirements</font></b>
</center>

<BR><BR>
<P><b>Indexicon is a tool capable of handling everyone's indexing needs.
Indexicon allows you to either create a general back-of-the-book index or
a more specialized user-controlled index.</b>
<p>
<center><B><A HREF="#FEATURES">Product  Features &amp;
Benefits</a>&#160;&#160;&#160; <IMG SRC="NEW_TINY.GIF"><A HREF="#NEW">What's
New in Version 2.5</a>&#160;&#160;&#160;
 <A HREF="#sysreq">System
Requirements</a></b></center></td></tr></table>

<BR><BR>
<A NAME="FEATURES">
<h2>Product Features and Benefits</h2>
<b>Indexicon Creates Indexes Automatically!</b>
<BR>
<blockquote>Indexicon takes the work out of indexing documents. There's no
need to re-read your text and manually tag significant terms, since
Indexicon locates important words and builds indexes for you.
<p>
With Indexicon, it is easy to produce consistent quality,
back-of-the-book indexes for every document: <p>
<ol>
<li>Indexicon automatically scans your document and marks the indexable terms.
<li>Indexicon uses Word's built-in-facility to compile the index that
appears at the end of your document.
<li>Indexicon allows the user to experiment with different levels of detail
and to vary the degree of comprehensiveness of the index.
<li>Indexicon's unique features allow the user to exclude portions of the
document from indexing and to edit the index entries.
</ol>

</blockquote>

<b>Easy to Install and Easy to Use</b>
<p><blockquote>
There's nothing to learn!  If you can click a mouse, you can index
a document of any size with Indexicon. <i>PC
Magazine</i> says, <i>with Indexicon, creating an index
is as quick and easy as spellchecking</i>. <b>
<p></blockquote>
Semantic and Syntactic Analysis</b>
<p><blockquote>
Indexicon disambiguates the English language.  Even when words
appear to be the same, such as <em>lead</em> the soft metal, and <em>lead</em>
to guide or influence, Indexicon recognizes the contextual difference
and indexes them accordingly.
<b></blockquote>
<p>
Quality Indexes Produced Quickly<blockquote>
<p></b><i>Indexicon is fast,</i> a reviewer for WINDOWS Magazine
states (10/94). <i> We created an index for a 50-page technical
manual in less than a minute.</i>  A task that would normally
take hours of tedious effort if done manually can now be done
effortlessly within a few minutes. <b>
<p></blockquote>
Economical Information Management
<p><blockquote>
</b> Indexicon-generated indexes will enable you to locate
specific information quickly while saving you time and money in production
costs and minimizing lengthy management tasks. You will appreciate
the efficiency and accuracy of Indexicon, as well as its compatibility
with <i>WordPerfect's </i>and <i>Microsoft Word's </i>indexing
features.</blockquote>


<center><i><font color=0000BB size=+1><b>Easily Creates Quality
Back-of-the-Book<BR> Indexes for Any Document!</b></font></i></center>


<BR><BR>
<A NAME="NEW"><h2>New Features for Indexicon 2.5</h2>
<ul type="square">
<li>The indexing process is 15-20% faster than version 2.0.
<li>20,000 new terms have been added to the primary lexicon.
<li>Double entries are automatically created for certain types of entries.
Where version 2.0 created an entry for "Byzantine architecture," version 2.5
will now create that entry as well as "Architecture: Byzantine."  Where
version 2.0 created an entry "Blue chip stocks," version 2.5 will, in
additon, create an entry for "Stocks, blue chip."
<li>Version 2.5 includes much more logic for recognizing personal names,
including logic for expanding partial name references.  If Indexicon 2.5
finds a reference to "Mr. Culpepper" in the text, it will now icnlude an
entry which expands the name to its fully indexable form, "Culpepper, Bradley
H.," if that complete form has been supplied elsewhere in the document.
<li>Pathnames, URLs, and e-mail addresses are now recognized.
<li>More sophisticated analysis is now done to determine the indexing value
of individual entries, resulting in a better distribution of entries across
indexing levels.</ul>
<b><i>New LexEdit features in Indexicon 2.5</b></i>
<ul type="square">
<li>Potential indexing values change according to the part of speech
selected for an entry.  For most parts of speech the indexing values are the
same ones that were available in earlier versions of LexEdit:  Rarely Index,
Sometimes Index, Always Index, etc.  But in other parts of speech the choices
change to reflect the special needs of that part of speech.  For instance, if
Personal Name is indicated as the part of speech, the available indexing
values are: First Name, Last Name, Famous Last Name, and Indexable as a
Single Name.
<li>Checkboxes have been added so that capitalization and abbreviation of
entries can be indicated.  This helps make the analysis process more accurate
and offers the user better control over indexing, especially the indexing of
proper nouns.</ul><br><br>

<a name="sysreq">
<H2>System Requirements</H2>
<b>Indexicon for 2.5 Microsoft &#174; Word 6.0</b>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft Word 6.0 for Windows
<li>386 or better CPU (486 recommended)
<li>Windows 3.11, Windows for Workgroups 3.11, Windows NT, or Windows 95
<li>8 MB RAM (16 MB RAM recommended for Windows 95)
<li>Win32s 1.30x (Windows 3.1 users only).  For more information see our
<a href="../TECHSUPP.HTM#Win32s">Technical Support area</a>
</ul>
<P>
<b>Indexicon 2.5 for Microsoft &#174; Word 7.0/97</b>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft Word 7.0 for Windows or Microsoft Word 97 for Windows
<li>486 CPU
<li>Windows 95 or Windows NT
<li>8 MB RAM (16 MB recommended)
</ul>
<P>
<b>Indexicon 2.0 for WordPerfect&#174;</b>
<ul>
<li>WordPerfect 6.1 for Windows
<li>386 or better CPU (486 recommended)
<li>Windows 3.11 or higher
<li>8 MB RAM
</ul>

<BR><BR><BR>

