<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="ABOOK.GIF" bgcolor="#ffffff"  link="#ooooff"
vlink="#663399">

<table width=600><tr>
<td valign=top width=150>
<a href="../INDEX.HTM"><img src="INDXHOME.GIF" border=0 alt="Indexicon HomePage"></A><BR>
<a href="SPECSHT.HTM"><img src="DESCRIP.GIF" border=0 alt="Description"></A><BR>
<a href="../DOMINION/INDEX_1.HTM"><img src="DEMO.GIF" border=0 alt="Download Demo"></A><BR>
<a href="REVIEWS.HTM"><img src="REVIEWS.GIF" border=0 alt="Reviews"></A><BR>
<a href="DEMOS.HTM"><img src="DEMOS.GIF" border=0 alt="Demonstrations"></A><BR>
<a href="ORDER.HTM"><img src="ORDER.GIF" border=0 alt="Order"></A><BR>
<a href="INDXFAQ.HTM"><img src="FAQ.GIF" border=0 alt="FAQ"></A><BR>
<a href="SPECSHT.HTM#sysreq"><img src="REQUIRE.GIF" border=0 alt="System Requirements"></A><BR>
<a href="TECHSUPP.HTM"><img src="SUPPORT.GIF" border=0 alt="Support"></A><BR>
<a href="../HOMEPAGE.HTM"><img src="ICVXHOME.GIF" border=0 alt="Iconovex HomePage"></A></td>
<td width=450 valign=top>
<center>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="INDXCN1.GIF" ALT="Indexicon Logo">
<BR><B><font size=+2 face=arial>Indexicon FAQ</font></b>
</center>
<BR><BR>
<P>Have questions about using Indexicon?  You've come to the right place!  We
also have tips on:
<ul>
<P><LI>using the <a href="REF_DOC.HTM">Reference Document</a> (RD) and
<a href="MASTER.HTM">Master Document</a> features in Word
<li>using the <a href="WPMASTER.HTM">Master Document</a> feature in
WordPerfect
<li>including chapter numbers in an index in either <a
href="CHAP_NUM.HTM">Word</a> or <a href="WPCHAP.HTM">WordPerfect</a>
</ul>
</td</tr></table>


<h2>Frequently Asked Question About Indexicon</h2>
<P>
<B>Q: </B>Now that I have installed Indexicon, where can I find it?<br>
<b>A: </b>Indexicon is found under the <b>Tools</b> menu from within Microsoft
Word. <p>
 <b>Q:</b>  Is the indexing <EM>fully</EM> automatic?<br> <b>A:</b>
The index generation is fully automatic.  However, the user can set certain
options and/or emphasize certain words to guarantee full control over the
final index. <P> <b>Q:</b>  How much information can it process at a
time?<br> <b>A:</b>  The amount of information that Indexicon is able to
process depends entirely on the speed of your processor, the amount of RAM
you have, the density of the document you are processing, and how
comprehensive you want the index. Generally, you can produce 1,000 or more
index entries without straining a typical system's resources. <P> <b>Q:</b>
Is the program independent from MS Word and WordPerfect?<br> <b>A:</b>  No.
Indexicon is an add-on that works in conjunction with both Word's and
WordPerfect's indexing features. <p> <b>Q:</b>  Can you edit the index and
the index entries?<br> <b>A:</b>  Yes.  The user maintains full control of
the final index.  An Entry Editor is provided as well as a utility to produce
specialized &quot;control lists.&quot; <p> <b>Q:</b>  Does Indexicon work
with FrameMaker?<br> <b>A:</b>  We are currently studying FrameMaker and plan
on producing an Indexicon product for it in the near future. <p> <b>Q:</b>
Does the user have control over the format of the final index?<br> <b>A:</b>
Yes.  The style of the index, including number of columns, etc., is
controlled through Word and WordPerfect's settings.  Indexicon will not override
any existing index styles.  We simply generate an index in the format specified
in the parent application.
<p>
<b>Q:</b>  How do I create an index for a master document or multiple file
projects using Indexicon with Microsoft Word?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Two ways:  <A HREF="REF_DOC.HTM">Reference Document Field (RD)</a> and <A HREF="MASTER.HTM">Master Document Field (MD).</a>
<p>
<b>Q:</b> How do I create an index for a master document or multiple file
projects using Indexicon with WordPerfect?<br>
<b>A:</b>  In WordPerfect, the only thing you can use is the <A
HREF="WPMASTER.HTM">Master Document Field (MD).</a>
<p>
<b>Q:</b> How do I include chapter numbers in the index using Microsoft Word or
WordPerfect?<br>
<b>A:</b> For <A HREF="CHAP_NUM.HTM">Microsoft Word.</a>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;For <A HREF="WPCHAP.HTM">WordPerfect.</a>
<p>
<b>Q:</b> If I already have index marks within a document, how should I use
Indexicon with this document?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Prior to manually editing the index, try removing all of the previous
index tags and run Indexicon on the document to see what kind of output is generated.
If you wish to leave the previous index tags in the document, Indexicon will
not replace the tags with its own.  Your index tags will be left as is.  If
necessary, you may import any previous &quot;control lists&quot; you may have, then create
an unknown word list, and then create a lexicon from those.  After all of that, you can
edit the entries.
<p>
<b>Q:</b>  Does Indexicon work with Doc-to-Help? <br>
<b>A:</b>  Yes.  We recommend using Indexicon first, then running Doc-to-Help to
add entries that Indexicon did not add.  Doc-to-Help's indexing feature is
pretty memory intensive and you can save time by running Indexicon first to place
index entries.  Doc-to-Help will recognize our index tags and convert them
to K-footnotes.  However, beware of the Remove TOC Bookmarks command.  If you
choose this option, Doc-to-Help alters the index tags so that Indexicon's
Entry Editor does not recognize them.  WexTech is aware of the problem and has put
it on their bug list.
<p>
<b>Q:</b>  What if I don't want to index the entire document?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Indexicon comes with a feature called the Exclusion Zone editor that
allows you to designate certain parts of the document that you do not wish to have
indexed.
<p>
<b>Q:</b>  Does Indexicon work with PageMaker?<br>
<b>A:</b>  No.  Sorry.
<P>

<BR><BR><BR>

