<h1 align=center><img src="TECH.GIF" ALT="Tech Support">
Iconovex Technical Support</H1>
<HR>
<P>
<b>Please read <a href="GENFAQ.HTM">the Iconovex FAQ (Frequently Asked
Questions)</a> or the FAQ for your product before sending a message to
Technical Support; your question may be answered there.</b>

<P>If you still have any technical questions, you can contact us quickly and
easily by filling out this <a href="#FORM">interactive form</A>. <i> Be sure
to specify which of our software products you are inquiring about.</i> If
your browser does not support forms, please feel free to call us at
1-800-943-0292 or e-mail us at:
<a href="mailto:fyi@iconovex.com">fyi@iconovex.com</a>. <p>

<P><BR><a name="Win32s"></a>
<h2>Win32s</H2>
You will need the latest version of Microsoft's Win32s extensions in order
to run Indexicon, WebAnchor, and AnchorPage under Windows 3.1. You can find
them at <a href="http://www.microsoft.com">Microsoft's web site</a> if you
wish, but as a convenience, you can
<a href="DOMINION/DLOADS/pw1118.exe">download them here</a>. <b>Be warned!</b>
This is a very large file (2.8 megabytes)!

<P>
To install Win32s, download the file PW1118.EXE (a self-extracting archive)
into an empty directory, "run" the file, and then run the "setup" program.
If you wish to remove Win32s from your system, go to Microsoft's site and
search for <b>Article Q120486</b>.  If you have problems installing or
running Win32s, search for <b>Article Q120901</b>.
<pre>

</pre>
