<html>
<head>
<title>System Requirements and Installation Instructions for Indexicon
Demo</title> </head> <body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<h2 align=center>Indexicon<sup>&#174;</sup> for MS Word for
Windows<sup>&#174;</sup> Demo <BR>
System Requirements and Installation Instructions</h2>

<BR><BR>
<center>
<a href="#sysreq">System Requirements</a> &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#install">Installation Instructions</a>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#remove">Removing the Demo</a>
</center>

<BR><BR>
<a name="sysreq">
<h2>System Requirements</h2>

<b>Indexicon 2.0 for Microsoft Word 6.0</b>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft Word 6.0 for Windows
<li>386 or better CPU (486 recommended)
<li>Windows 3.11, Windows for Workgroups 3.11, Windows NT, or Windows 95
<li>8 MB RAM (16 MB RAM recommended for Windows 95)
<li>Win32s 1.30x (Windows 3.1 users only).  For more information see our
<a href="../../TECHSUPP.HTM#Win32s">Technical Support area</a> <p>
</ul>

<P>
<b>Indexicon 2.0 for Microsoft Word 7.0</b>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft Word 7.0 for Windows
<li>486 CPU
<li>Windows 95 or Windows NT
<li>8 MB RAM (16 MB recommended)
</ul>


<a name="install">
<h2>How to Install the Demo </h2>

<ol>
<li>Download the demo file (for Word 6.0, INDXICON.EXE, for Word 7.0,
INDEXW7.EXE) into a temporary directory.
<li>At a DOS prompt, navigate to the directory where you saved the demo file
and type the name of the file, i.e., INDXICON or INDEXW7.  The setup program
will then be extracted from the file you downloaded.
<li>From the Program or File Manager in Windows 3.1 or Windows NT,
choose <b>Run</b>. In Windows 95, click <b>Start</b> and then choose
<b>Run</b>.
<li>In the Run box type <b>c:\temp\setup.exe</b> ("temp" being the directory
where you extracted the setup files) and then click <B>OK</b>.

<li>IMPORTANT: Notepad will open and you will be presented with a copy of the
Indexicon Limited Evaluation License Agreement.  By installing Indexicon, you
agree to the terms and conditions of the agreement.  Once you have read the
agreement and agree to the terms and conditions, close Notepad before
continuing with the installation.

<li>Click <B>Accept</b>.
<li>At the next screen, choose <B>Continue</b>.
<li>Select <b>Install Indexicon</b> and <B>Continue</b>.

<li>Follow the instructions on the screen.

<li>Review the README.TXT for last minute updates and changes.
<li>Once Indexicon is installed, it can be launched from the <b>Tools</b>
menu from within Microsoft Word. </ol>


<a name="remove">
<h2>How to Remove the Demo </h2>

<ol>
<li>Run the setup program (SETUP.EXE).
<li>The license agreement will be displayed.  Close Notepad and in the setup
program, click <b>Accept</b>.
<li>Click <b>Continue</b>.
<li>Select <b>Remove Indexicon</b> and click <b>Continue</b>.
<li>Click <b>Continue</b> again.
<li>Follow the instructions on the screen.

<BR><BR>
<BR><hr><br>
