<TITLE>Indexicon PC Magazine Review</title>
</head>

<body BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" link="#0000FF" vlink="#663399">

<h1><center>PC Magazine Reviews Indexicon</h1></center>

<hr width=80% align=center><center><b>Word Processing Add-On</b></center>
<hr width=80% align=center>

<p><h2>Indexicon Indexes Documents
Quickly</h2>

<b>by David Haskins</b>
<br><i>PC Magazine</i>. September 14, 1994
<br>Reprinted with permission. Copyright Ziff-Davis Publishing Company L.P.

<p>
Indexicon for WordPerfect for Windows 6.0,
Version 1.0 ($149.99), is a smart but still-evolving word processor add-on
that makes creating indexes simple. This capablity makes long business
documents more useful and saves time and money for those creating
opuses.
<br>. . .
<br>The program generates an index by using its 55,000-word dictionary and
extensive set of rules for determining parts of speech and key concepts to
analyze each sentence and determine the most important words and phrases.
Indexicon's speed is impressive, particularly when compared with
professional indexers, who typically index between three and six pages per
hour. On a 33-MHz 486 with 16MB of RAM, Indexicon created an index for a
50-page, single-spaced document to three levels of detail in 6 minutes 30
seconds.
<p>While the result is generally an accurate and
thorough index, it requires polishing . . . But even with manual cleanup,
Indexicon took a fraction of the time and cost of professional indexing.
<br>. . .<br>


