<HEAD>
<TITLE>Indexicon Press Releases</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><U>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</U>
<h3><center>ICONOVEX ANNOUNCES THE RELEASE OF INDEXICON 2.0 WITH NEW
     FEATURES FOR MORE VERSATILE INDEXING</center></h3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Bloomington, MN -- Iconovex Corporation, leaders in intelligent
 abstracting software, today announced the release of Indexicon 2.0 for
 Microsoft Word 6.0 for Windows.  Indexicon is the first and only
 software that can actually read and understand the subtleties of the
 English language.  The software integrates into the tools menu, and
 allows users to create an automatic index at the click of a mouse,
 making quick work of the most daunting, time-consuming tasks.  Based
 on Iconovex's proprietary parsing technology, Indexicon uses
 syntactical rules and semantic weight-in-context -- not simple
 statistical calculations of word frequency -- to analyze document
 content, identify the significant words and phrases and build a
 back-of-the-book style index automatically.  With new features for
 added ease and user control, Indexicon can make indexing a document as
 easy as spellchecking.<P>  Indexicon 2.0 is much faster and more robust
        than its predecessor, and it creates indexes that are more
        complete and accurate.  Version 2.0 is especially improved in
        its handling of proper nouns and personal names.  New features
include a full-function Index Entry Editor which allows users to easily
find and modify and index entry and new paragraph-by-paragraph processing
which includes a built-in utility for creating and maintaining "control"
lists, terms that the user considers particularly important (or unimportant)
for indexing purposes.  Using control lists to alter the indexing
process, users can now automatically build indexes that reflect the
particular priorities of their own fields and specialties.<P>  "With the
addition of our full-function entry editor, we have created a versatile
tool that will fulfill everyone's indexing needs," says Bernardo
Sotomayor, vice president and general manager of Iconovex.  "Indexicon
2.0 can be used by the student who wants the ease of a fully automatic
indexer, yet it's a suitably sophisticated tool for the professional
writer who wants to control every detail of the final index." <P>
Indexicon 2.0 joins the Iconovex product line of natural language
processing programs which includes Syntactica, the parsing engine upon
which Indexicon is based, and AnchorPage, the only automatic indexing,
abstracting and hyperlinking software available for the World Wide Web.<P>
Indexicon 2.0 sells for $129 and is available through premiere resellers and
distributors.  A version for WordPerfect 6.1 will be available in
February, 1996.  Order direct by calling the Iconovex Corporation at (800)
943-0292 or by email <a
href="mailto:fyi@iconovex.com">fyi@iconovex.com</a>.  For a limited time,
free 30-day evaluation copies of Indexicon 2.0 are <A
HREF="http://dominion.iconovex.com">available for downloading</a>. The
Iconovex Corporation is a software development company and a wholly-owned
subsidiary of Innovex, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin-film disk drive market.
</BLOCKQUOTE><hr>
<pre>
Contact:                                Contact:
Robert Griggs                           Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner
Vice President Sales and Marketing      EBS Public Relations
Iconovex Corporation                    708-714-8600
612-896-5109
</pre>
