<HEAD>
<TITLE>Indexicon Press Releases</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><U>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</U>
<center><h3>NEW PRODUCT OFFERS FULLY AUTOMATIC INDEXING AT THE CLICK OF A MOUSE</h3></center>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Bloomington, MN.  ICONOVEX Corporation announces the release of
Indexicon, the first fully automatic indexing software.   Currently
available in versions for WordPerfect for Windows, Microsoft Word
for Windows, and Microsoft Word for the Macintosh, Indexicon &quot;reads&quot;
the user's document, locates the significant terms and phrases,
and generates a back-of-the-book style index, all at the click of a
mouse.  Using syntactic and semantic analysis, Indexicon is able
to disambiguate language; it can distinguish, for instance, when
the term &quot;lead&quot; means to take followers in hand and
when that same term refers to the common metal.
<P>
&quot;Indexicon
produces a fully detailed, comprehensive index every time,&quot;says
Robert Griggs, vice president of sales and marketing for ICONOVEX.
 &quot;And it's so fast and easy to use that no one who creates
or manages documents will ever again consider a significant document
complete until it has an index.&quot;
<P>
Indexicon is fully automatic.
 Other indexing products require that the user painstakingly review
documents line by line and mark index entries manually, or create
a concordance file from which an index can be built. With Indexicon,
the user simply sets the level of detail he or she prefers, and
the software does the rest.  A chore that would page two take hours of
tedious effort if done manually, can now be done in a few minutes
with no effort at all. Indexicon integrates seamlessly with
WordPerfect 6.0, Microsoft Word and MS Word for Mac.  Once installed,
it becomes an item on the Tools menu with its own cascading submenu of options.
And because it's fully integrated, Indexicon allows the user to take advantage of the
other word processing features to control the shape and even the
content of the final index.  The user indicates formatting preferences
in the Define Index dialog box.  Content can be controlled through
Indexicon's adjustable level of detail or by using Indexicon in
conjunction with the manual indexing features.  The user can,
for instance, mark several terms or phrases she wishes to give
emphasis, then run Indexicon on the document.  The resulting index
will include the usergenerated entries as well as Indexicon's
selections.
<p>
Indexicon costs $249 and is available through a network
of resellers or direct at 1-800-943-0292.
<p>
The ICONOVEX Corporation is a software development company and a
wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the world's leading manufacturer
of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive market.
<p></BLOCKQUOTE>
