<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Step 1 </TITLE>
<LINK REL="Next" HREF="STEP2.HTM">
<LINK REL="Previous" HREF="TUTOR.HTM"></HEAD>
<BODY background="BLUEBACK.GIF" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"
LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>Step 1&#151;Open Indexicon</B></CENTER></H1>

<blockquote>
<P>When you open Indexicon from the Tools menu, you will first see this
screen.  From here you select <B>Create Index </B>to begin creating your
index.  From this screen can also edit existing index
entries with the <A HREF="INDEXED.HTM">Index Entry Editor</A>, exclude parts
of a document you don&#146;t want to be indexed with the
<A HREF="EXCLUED.HTM">Exclusion Zone Editor</A>, and open
<A HREF="LEXEDIT.HTM">LexEdit</A>, where you can build your own lexicons to
use with Indexicon.
</blockquote>

<P ALIGN=CENTER> <CENTER> <IMG
SRC="STEP1002.GIF" WIDTH = 344 HEIGHT = 262 ALT="Indexicon main dialog"></CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<center>
<A
HREF="TUTOR.HTM"><B><img src="HANDAR3.GIF" alt="Previous Page"
border=0>&#160;Previous Page</B></A>&#160;&#160;&#160; <A
HREF="STEP2.HTM"><B>Next Step <img src="HANDAR4.GIF" alt="Next Step"
border=0></B></A> </center>

