<TITLE>Indexicon Samples</TITLE>
<LINK REL="Next" HREF="SAMP1.HTM">
<LINK REL="Previous" HREF="DEMOS.HTM"></HEAD>
<BODY background="BLUEBACK.GIF" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"
LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>Sample Indexes</B></CENTER></H1>

<blockquote>
<P>Here we provide samples of indexes produced with Indexicon.  In order to
give you an accurate idea of Indexicon's capabilities, we have indexed each
of the documents at several different levels of comprehensiveness (Indexicon
provides 6 levels). No entries have been manually added to the index, though
some entries have been edited and some others removed, so you should be able
to get a clear picture of the type of information that Indexicon will index
automatically.  If this were a professional index, we would of course add
other entries for topics that Indexicon missed or for topics that aren't
mentioned literally in the text.
<P>
In each case we attempt to provide a fair estimate of how much time was
involved in the whole process.  These indexes were produced using Indexicon
2.0 for Microsoft Word 6.0, on a 486 with 16 RAM.

<P>The first set of sample indexes were created from document on
oceanography (3,507 words), indexed at <A HREF="SAMPLE1.HTM#s1lev1">Level
1</A>, <A HREF="SAMPLE1.HTM#s1lev3"> Level 3</A>, and <A
HREF="SAMPLE1.HTM#s1lev5">Level 5</A>.

<P>The second set of indexes were created from a document excerpt on
photography (6,658 words), indexed at <A HREF="SAMPLE2.HTM#s2lev1">Level
1</A>, <A HREF="SAMPLE2.HTM#s2lev3"> Level 3</A>, and <A
HREF="SAMPLE2.HTM#s2lev5">Level 5</A>. </blockquote>

<BR><BR>
