 <HEAD>
<TITLE>Iconovex Fact Sheet</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!-- RTFact 1.3 Iconovex Corporation 1995 -->

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
<CENTER><img src="ICONBAR.GIF"></CENTER>
<P>
<table>
<tr>
<td><b>Fact Sheet</b></td><td><pre>
                                  </pre></td>
<td><b>Summer 1996</b></td>
</tr></table>

<P>

ICONOVEX Corporation, a software development company located in Bloomington,
Minnesota, produces software programs that automate the processing, indexing
and summarizing of English text documents.  ICONOVEX Corporation has 23
employees.
<P>

<P>

ICONOVEX Corporation is a wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the
world's leading manufacturer of lead wire assemblies for the high-growth
thin film disk drive market. Founded 1972, INNOVEX has over 500 employees.
NASDAQ Symbol: INVX.
<P>

<P>

<h3><center>Product Overview</center></h3>
<P>
<blockquote>
<B>EchoSearch</B>
<br>
EchoSearch&#153;, our second award-winning product, is the first search
accelerator that allows you to search the web faster, smarter, and easier.
It uses multiple search engines and our proprietary linguistic analysis to
select and prioritize the most relevant hits for your review.  You no longer
have to pull up list after list of hits that are unrelated to your search.
These <I>Qualified Results</I> are then presented to you in a hyperlinked
format that very easily allows you to navigate the documents most relevant
to your search.  EchoSearch searches on <I>ideas</I> not just words.
<P>

<B>
AnchorPage</B>
<br>

The award-winning AnchorPage&#174;, from Iconovex, is the only automatic
hypertext indexing and abstracting software to use true linguistic analysis
to extract the significant phrases, concepts, and ideas from HTML documents.
This linguistic analysis allows individuals to organize large amounts of
information quickly, efficiently, and reliably into four different
organizational views of the information (Table of Contents, Phrase, Concept,
and Summary Views).  By applying the rules of the English language and
analyzing the individual words in their context, AnchorPage is able to
&quot;read&quot; and understand documents and provide concise synopsis or
summary of the information contained within.  AnchorPage automatically
organizes information on your internal or external Web sites while easing
the frustration users experience in locating specific information.
AnchorPage also decreases the amount of system resources used by search
engines.
<P>

<B>Indexicon</B>
<br>
For single document users, ICONOVEX released a shrink-wrapped version of
the Syntactica technology,  Indexicon, priced at $129, is the only fully
automatic indexing software.  Indexicon finds key terms within a document,
then builds a Back-of-the-Book style index which displays those key terms
alphabetically and by page number.  Its ease of use and seamless integration
are making Indexicon a big hit with end users.  ICONOVEX Corporation is
currently shipping Indexicon for Windows versions of WordPerfect 6.1,
Microsoft Word 6.0 and Word 7.0 available through our premiere network of
resellers or call us directly.
<P>

<B>
Syntactica Web API (SWAPI)</B>
<br>

The Syntactica Web API (SWAPI) is a C language interface to a library that
enables client applications to perform linguistic analysis of data and HTML
based documents while automatically hyperlinking the various forms of
linguistic output back to the original source data. The available linguistic
outputs are Indexes, Concepts, Summary, and Table of Contents. The
hyperlinking is done using standard HTML 2.0 conventions and can be read by
any HTML 2.0 compliant browser.
<P>

The primary goals of SWAPI are to:
<P>

<UL>
<LI> Provide a high level API to perform linguistic analysis, hyperlinking
and formatting on HTML and other data<p>
<LI> Provide flexibility and ease of use to SWAPI Client Application
developers<p>
<LI> Be functionally equivalent across all platforms
</UL>
<p>
SWAPI is built as a layer of abstraction over the Syntactica API (SAPI).
SAPI is a lower level interface to Syntactica - ICONOVEX's parsing and
linguistic analysis engine.
<P>

<B>Syntactica API (SAPI)</B><B> </B>
<P>

The Syntactica API (SAPI) is a C language interface to a library that
enables client applications to perform linguistic analysis of ASCII data and
automatically produce four different linguistic outputs; Indexes, Concepts,
and Summary.  SAPI is similar to SWAPI discussed above, but is a lower level
interface to Syntactica - Iconovex's proprietary parsing and linguistic
analysis engine.  SAPI permits the OEMs to integrate at a lower level and
have the ability to fine tune the analysis engine.
</blockquote>
<P>

<P>
