<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff"  link="#ooooff" vlink="#663399">
<center><img src="APGLOBE1.GIF" alt=AnchorPage align=middle></center>
<EM><h2><center>AnchorPage FAQs</h2></center>
<P>
</B></EM>
<OL>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Is this a search engine like Yahoo?<br>
<b>A:</b>  No.  AnchorPage is a complement to a search engine in that we
&quot;intelligently&quot; analyze documents and then search engines can be
used against our &quot;smart&quot; indexes.
<P>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Is this an HTML authoring tool?<br>
<b>A:</b>  No.  We help organize HTML pages once they are created so that the
information is easier to access for users of your site.
<P>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Does this product run on my server?<br>
<b>A:</b>  No, AnchorPage does not reside on the server.  Each person who
will be using AnchorPage to organize information must have a copy on their
machine.
<P>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How can I get AnchorPage to generate only 1 segment per document I
want processed?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Set the segment size very high.  For example, set it at 30000.
<P>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How can I get AnchorPage to generate only 1 segment for all the
documents I want processed?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Set the segment size to 0.
<P>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Can you get reference page numbers using AnchorPage?<br>
<b>A:</b>  You can identify document names, but due to the dynamic nature of
hypertext, page numbers become obsolete.
<hr>
<a href="/HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="ICONHOME.GIF" alt=Return align=middle>Return to
the Iconovex HomePage</a>
<p><address>July 17, 1996 cml@iconovex.com</address>

