<html>
<head>
<title>"Cryptography's Role in Securing the Information Society"</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<h2>Cryptography's Role in Securing the Information Society</h2>
<hr>
<p>
<H3><a href="CRYPTO/HOME.HTM">The Recommendation of the NAS Regarding 
Cryptography</a></H3 <P>
Even as you read this, Congress is debating the laws governing and effecting
cryptography, particularly in as much as it relates to the Internet and
electronic commerce, making this a issue of much concern for many members
of the internet community.  Congress commissioned the NAS (National Academy
of Sciences) to study the issue of cryptography and make some sort of
recommendation as to how Congress should proceed; the NAS turned the issue
over to the National Research Council of its Computer Science and
Telecommunications Board, and here is the preliminary, pre-publication
result.
<p>
For further information, or to read the full text of the report,
 you can visit the <A HREF="http://www.nas.edu"><I>NAS Home Page.</I></A>
<p>
<blockquote><i>Reprinted with permission from CRYPTOGRAPHY'S ROLE IN SECURING
THE INFORMATION SOCIETY. Copyright 1996 by the National Academy
of Sciences. Courtesy of the Computer Science and Telecommunications
Board and the National Academy Press.</i></blockquote>


<p>
<ul>
<li>Phrase, Concept, Abstract, and Table of Contents Views were selected.
<li>All Selectivity levels were set at "3."
<li>Phrase Horizontal and Phrase Circular links were selected.
<li>Both Phrase and Concept "A to Z" pages were used.
<li>A customized lexicon was incorporated.
<li>The "Arizona" icon template set was used.
</ul>
<p>

