<title>
Telecommunications Competition and Deregulation Act of 1996
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><h2>Telecommunications Competition and Deregulation Act of 1996
(Signed by President Clinton)</h2></center>
<hr>
<h3><a href="TELCOM/TOC.HTM">Telecommunications Competition and
Deregulation Act of 1996</a></h3>
This is full hypertext version of the actual bill (taken from the Thomas
Website), passed by the Senate and the House of Representatives, and 
recently signed by President Clinton.  This bill contains the
controversial Title IV--"Obscene, Harrassing, and Wrongful
Utilization of Telecommunications Facilities," also known by the Short Title
"The Communications Decency Act of 1995."
