<html>
<head><title>Upcoming EchoSearch Features</title></head> <BODY
background="SPOTS.GIF">
<center><h1>Upcoming Features</h1></center> <HR>
<p>We are currently working on the following enhancements and new features
for EchoSearch.  Most, if not all, of these additions will be included in
version 2.0, due out the first quarter of 1997.</p> <ul
type="circ">
<li>Frames added to output pages so that the navigational window and
summarization window will be visible at all times.</li></ul> <p>
<center><table cellpadding=4 cols=3><td><font=-1>Navigation<br>
Window</font><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="4RIGHT.GIF"><pre>



</pre><font=-1>Summarization<br>
Window</font><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img
src="4RIGHT.GIF"></td><td><img
src="FRAMES.GIF"></td><td><font=-1>Document<br>
Window</font><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img
src="4LEFT.GIF"></td></tr></table></center>
<b>1.) Navigation Window</b>  This window contains icons that allow you to
choose which view to use in displaying the output (Qualified Results,
Concepts, Summaries, or Index).  There is also an AZ navigation bar that
allows you to jump to the entries for any given letter.<br><b>2.)
Summarization Window</b>  This window displays the various types of output
and acts as your starting point for clicking through the results.  Just click
on any hotlinked term or concept and you will be taken to that term or
concept in the document.<br><b>3.) Document Window</b>  This window
displays the original document (minus the graphics).  After you click on
a term or concept in the Summarization window, the Document window will
display the document with the term or concept you have chosen at the
top of the frame.<ul type="circ">
 <p><li>Improved document summaries. The summaries of
the documents most relevant to your query are listed first.</li> <p>
<li>Better document and session management, including incremental additions
to sessions (i.e., allowing users to include an additonal number of documents
to an existing session).</li> <p><li>Allow queries to be scheduled.</li> <p>
<li>Bookmarks can be transfered between EchoSearch and your browser and vice
versa.</li> <p> <li>Enable EchoSearch to use subscriber search engines
(Britanica Online, Electric Library) as well as public ones, with username
and password supplied by user.</li><p> <li>Intermediate results are generated
so output can be viewed while results are still being generated.  In other
words, EchoSearch will show you the processed results for the first couple of
documents while it continues to download and process remaining
documents.</li><p> <li>Improved advanced search capabilities.</li>
 </ul> <p> <HR> <center><H3><IMG SRC="HOT.GIF" BORDER="0"
HEIGHT="43" WIDTH="79"><A HREF="ESDOWNLOAD.HTM">Download a non-expiring
evaluation copy of EchoSearch 1.07 for Windows 95 or Windows NT
here!</A></H3></center>
<hr> <p>
<center><a href="echo.map"><img src="MENU.JPG" border=0 alt="Navigation Menu"
ISMAP></center></a><pre>

