<HEAD>
<TITLE>Description of EchoSearch</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="SPOTS.GIF">
<table><tr><td align="LEFT"><a
href="http://cafe.symantec.com/javacentral/index.html"> <img
src="CAFELOGO.GIF" alt="Cafe Logo"></a><BR> <a
href="http://cafe.symantec.com/javacentral/index.html"> <i>EchoSearch is
Built with Symantec
Cafe</a><sup>tm</sup></i></td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td
align="RIGHT"><img src="CHEETAH2.JPG"></td></tr></table><hr> <p> <font
size=+2><b>Introducing EchoSearch. . . </B></font> the metasearch tool that
enables you to find what you're looking for on the Web faster and more
reliably. </P><P> EchoSearch is a truly remarkable product. With EchoSearch,
you will no longer need to sort through uninformative hit list descriptions
looking for the documents that <I>might</I> contain the information you want.
You won't need to point your browser at those documents, one after another,
to check their content. EchoSearch uses multiple search engines
simultaneously, in about the same time it would take you to use only one
engine, to build a complete hit list. Then it simultaneously downloads and
analyzes those documents and presents you with a list of concepts related to
your query. Find the concept you're interested in, click on it, and you are
instantly taken to the relevant portion of the relevant document.</P>

<UL> <LI>EchoSearch is <I>accurate</I>
because its unique, proprietary engine actually filters hits from popular
search engines according to the <I>meaning</I> (concept, phrase or summary)
you are searching for.</LI>
<p>
<LI>Your searches take less time because rather than having to go to each
individual URL that came up as a hit, you just go through the index view
generated by EchoSearch and select from the entries that closely match your
query.  This eliminates wasting time with hits that have little relevance to
you.
</LI>
</UL><font size=+2 color="RED"><b>EchoSearch will revolutionize the
way you search!</font></b>

<UL>
<LI>Searches with multiple search engines like AltaVista, Excite, HotBot,
Infoseek, Lycos, OpenText, and WebCrawler simultaneously.
</LI>
<LI>Searches Usenet articles as well as the World Wide Web.
</LI>
<LI>Gives you convenient methods of making Boolean queries using &quot;and&quot;,
&quot;or,&quot; etc.
</LI>
<LI>Searches results are automatically displayed within your browser.
</LI>
<LI>Automatically downloads hit documents to your computer during the search,
so you can read them directly without going back through the web for each one.
</LI>
<LI>Supports proxy servers.</LI>
<LI>Automatically converts your evaluation copy to a purchased
copy with a simple phone call.
<LI>Gives free online upgrades to registered users.</LI>
<p></UL>
<center><font size=+1>Check out even more <A HREF="FEATURES.HTM">upcoming
EchoSearch features</A>.</font> </center><P>
 </P><P>

<font size=+2 color="RED"><B>The Price is Right!</B></font>
</P><P>
</P><BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>At just <font size=+1><b>$29.95*</b></font> or <font
size=+1><b>$49.95*</b></font>, EchoSearch is easily within your grasp.</P> <P>
<b><font size=+1>*</b></font> see <A HREF="ESORDER.HTM#UPGRADE">Online
Upgrade Options</A> for details.<p> </BLOCKQUOTE></TABLE> <HR> <H3
