<H1><center>EchoSearch Sample Output</h1></center>
<hr>
This trial run of EchoSearch was done on the query <i>Magellan
+Venus</b>.  Below is the main screen. Search terms are entered in the <b><i>Search for</b></i> box.
Boolean operators, as used in <i>+Venus</i> below, can easily be added to
queries through the <B><I>Advanced Search</b></i> dialog. For multiple words,
you would enclose the query in quotes (i.e., "<i>search engines</i>"). The
<b><i>Return documents</b></i> box allows you to enter the number of
documents that you want EchoSearch to return for any given query. <p> To see some of the
EchoSearch screens and to learn about how EchoSearch processes, click
