<body>
<h2>GATT: "General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade"</h2><p>
<hr>
<h3><A HREF="GATT/index.htm">GATT<sup>*</sup></A></H3>
<sup>*</sup>This document consisted of 59 html files = roughly 1.16 MB; it 
was run through <cite>AnchorPage</cite> with:<ul>
<li>WebAnchor's selectivity level was set at "2."
<li>The "default" template was used.
</ul>
<strong>These options give GATT '94 greater accessibility. Since it is a
large document, the mid-range Selectivity Levels were chosen to ensure that
all of the significant phrases and concepts were selected without many
extraneous entries. Both a Concept and a Phrase View "A to Z" page were
chosen to allow searching through the document for significant ideas
without having to download the entire document. Once you find a
concept you are interested in the Circular Concept links allow you to trace
it through the entire document.</strong>

<h3><A HREF="GATT/gatt1947.htm">GATT 1947</A></H3>
<ul><li>For virtue of comparison here is the GATT 1947 agreement in its
entirety. It HAS NOT been run through Anchor Page. It consists of one html
file equaling 185K so...<br><strong>PLEASE NOTE: this is one very large 
document and will take a while to download.
</STRONG></ul>

</ul><hr> 
