<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff"  link="#ooooff" vlink="#663399">
<center><img src="../WEBANCH.GIF" alt=WebAnchor aling=middle></center>
<EM><center><h2>WebAnchor FAQs</center></h2>
</EM><P>
<OL>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How is this product different from AnchorPage?<br>
<b>A:</b>  WebAnchor only offers the Phrase View of a document where AnchorPage
offers the Phrase, Concept, Table of Contents, and Abstract views.  WebAnchor
is also an end-user product.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Can I use WebAnchor to index an entire website?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Yes.  WebAnchor can take an entire website and create a fully-hyperlinked
index listing the important terms and phrases contained within the site.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b> Can WebAnchor index information across networks (LANs/WANs)?<br>
<b>A:</b> No.  WebAnchor will take any HTML documents that you have on a given
PC and index that information only.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b> Is WebAnchor a search engine?<br>
<b>A:</b> No.  WebAnchor creates static indexes of information that you would, in
turn, publish on a Web site.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b> Does WebAnchor reside on a server?<br>
<b>A:</b> No.  Each person who uses WebAnchor to index and organize information
must have a copy on his/her machine.
<p>
<hr>
<a href="/HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="../ICONHOME.GIF" alt=Return 
align=middle>Return to the Iconovex HomePage</a>
<p><address>July 10, 1996 cml@iconovex.com</address>

</BODY>

</HTML>
</DOC>
