<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff"  link="#ooooff" vlink="#663399">
<center><img src="ICONBAR.GIF" alt=Iconovex align="middle"></center>
<center><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2></center>
<P>

<P>
<OL>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How can I purchase one of your products?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Call us at 1-800-943-0292, fill out the contact information on our
web site at http://www.iconovex.com, or email us at sales@iconovex.com.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How can I become a BETA tester?<br>
<b>A:</b>  BETA versions of our software are usually available for downloading
from our Web site, usually under the &quot;What's New&quot; category.  You
could also email us at fyi@iconovex.com.  Be sure to include your name, email address,
regular address, and your phone number.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  What are the minimum system requirements needed to run your products?<br>
<b>A:</b>  For Windows 3.1x, most of our products require a 486 CPU, 8 MB RAM, 10
MB available disk space, and Win32s 1.3x.  For Windows NT, most products require
a minimum of 16 MB RAM.  For Windows 95, most products require a minimum of 8
MB RAM.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  How does the software decide which words it will include in the
index?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Iconovex uses a linguistic analysis engine that &quot;reads&quot;
electronic documents and can identify important words, word phrases, and ideas.
The output is based on word meaning rather than word frequency.  Controls such as
Level of Detail and user lexicons allow you, the user, to influence the indexing
decisions.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Where do I get upgrades?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Upgrades and how to get them are announced on our Web site.  If you
have any further question regarding upgrades, you can call us at 1-800-943-0292.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Which product(s) do I use to produce an online index?<br>
<b>A:</b>  AnchorPage and WebAnchor process HTML documents, allowing users to
create online indexes for these documents.  AnchorPage and WebAnchor, however, do
not convert existing index entries in RTF documents.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Which product(s) do I use to produce an index for a word processed
document?<br>
<b>A:</b>  Indexicon works as an add-on for both MS Word and WordPerfect.
Back-of-the-book style indexes can be produced in minutes where manual indexing
would take hours.  Users can implement the Entry Editor and/or use &quot;control
lists&quot; to improve the quality of the output.
<p>
<LI><b>Q:</b>  Do I need Win32s to run any of the programs?<br>
<b>A:</b>  If you are using one of our 32-bit applications with a 16-bit operating
system (such as Windows 3.1x), you will need to install Win32s in order to run the
program.  Win32s can be downloaded from the Iconovex website at
http://www.iconovex.com/TECHSUPP.HTM or from the Microsoft site at http://www.microsoft.com.
<p>
<hr>
<a href="HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="ICONHOME.GIF" alt=Return align=middle>Return to
the Iconovex HomePage</a>
<p><address>July 10, 1996 cml@iconovex.com</address>

</body>
</html>

