<HEAD>
<TITLE>LexEdit </TITLE>
<LINK REL="Next" HREF="STEP3.HTM">
<LINK REL="Previous" HREF="EXCLUDED.HTM"></HEAD>
<BODY background="BLUEBACK.GIF" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000"
LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER><B>LexEdit</B></CENTER></H1>

<blockquote>
<P>LexEdit is a tool with which you can create your own personalized
lexicons or &quot;control lists&quot; to use with Indexicon.  Indexicon has
its own primary lexicon that it refers to when making its indexing decisions.
By creating your own lexicons, you can alter how Indexicon indexes particular
words.  Perhaps you don&#146;t want a word indexed as often or maybe you want
every instance of a word indexed.  LexEdit is also used with the Unknown Words
feature; import the Unknown Words list from a document into LexEdit and you
can then attach values and grammatical information to words that Indexicon
did not recgonize. </blockquote>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="LEXEDIT.GIF" ALT="LexEdit main screen"></CENTER>

<P><BR><BR> <P><center>
