<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P>

<P>

<EM>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</EM><p>
<center>
<h3>ICONOVEX'S ECHOSEARCH WINS BYTE MAGAZINE'S BEST OF COMDEX AWARD</h3>
</center>
<P>

<B><I>Marks Second Straight Spring Comdex Win</B></I><B>
<P>

<P>

</B><B></B>Chicago, IL -- June 5, 1996 -- Byte Magazine today announced that
<B> Iconovex Corporation</B> has won its second straight Best of Comdex/
Spring Award.  The award was presented to Iconovex, recognizing its new
product, <B>EchoSearch, </B>as Best Internet Product.  At Spring Comdex 1995
in Atlanta, GA, Iconovex's <B>AnchorPage</B> won the same award in the Best
Development Software category.  Iconovex Corporation is a subsidiary of
Innovex, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), a leading producer of lead wire assemblies for
the thin film disk drive market.
<P>

EchoSearch is an intelligent desktop-based search engine tool for browsers
of the Web that significantly improves the speed and accuracy of searches.
A simple, yet powerful tool, EchoSearch is ideal for <I>all</I> users
searching the Internet or a corporate Intranet for information.  EchoSearch
is one of the first truly &quot;full blown&quot; Java applications.  It
makes use of the programming language's multi-threading capabilities,
enabling users to simultaneously query multiple search engines.  Unlike
other search engines, EchoSearch features an intelligent back-end that can
index and accurately summarize the documents gathered, avoiding the
necessity of the user downloading entire sets of documents in order to
ascertain the relevance to the query.
<P>

&quot;We are quite excited that EchoSearch was recognized for its
innovative technology by such a distinguished, highly regarded publication,
&quot; says Bernardo Sotomayor, vice president and general manager of
Iconovex. &quot;We are fortunate in having made the decision two years ago
to embrace the Web, and the Internet in general, as our primary target
platforms.&quot;
<P>

Byte's Best of COMDEX awards program has become a time honored tradition in
the computer industry after eight years of presentations.  In evaluating
products, Byte editors search out
innovative new products that show strong potential to influence and impact
the computer industry worldwide.
<P>

&quot;Byte Magazine reaches a large number of technology professionals that
are constantly searching  and sifting through the wealth of information that
is available online,&quot; adds Sotomayor.  &quot;These users are in need of
a tool that can help them sort through and find relevant information.
EchoSearch addresses this need with a tool that will not only find
information, but synthesize and distill it as well.&quot;
<P>

EchoSearch will be available in July, 1996 for a suggested retail price of $
49.95.  For additional information, contact Iconovex Corporation at 800-94
3-0292, on the Web at http://www.iconovex.com, or via E-mail at fyi@
iconovex.com.  EchoSearch joins the highly acknowledged Iconovex product
line, which includes AnchorPage&#174;, WebAnchor&#153;, and SWAPI&#153;, all
of which are based on Syntactica&#174;, Iconovex's proprietary indexing and
abstracting engine.
<P>
<b><a href="ECHO/ESDOWNLOAD.HTM">Click here to download an evaluation 
copy of EchoSearch.</a></b> <P>

<B><I>Iconovex Corporation, makers of software that understands ideas, is a
software development company and a wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc.,
the world's leading manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film
disk drive market, and Innomedica, Inc., manufacturers of medical devices
for OEM customers.</B></I>

<p>
