<HEAD>
<TITLE>Announcing EchoSearch</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!-- RTFact 1.3 Iconovex Corporation 1995 -->

<BODY>
<pre><b>
					     	Contact:
					     	Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner
					     	EBS Public Relations, Inc.
					     	847-714-8600
</b></pre>
<P>

<b><em>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b></em>
<center><img src="TEMPBAR.GIF">
<h2>Iconovex Corp. Introduces EchoSearch Web Software</h2>
<P>

<B><I>The First Truly Intelligent Desktop Search Tool</B></I></center>
<P>

<P>

<I>Bloomington, MN - </I>Iconovex Corporation, makers of software
that understands ideas, announces <B>EchoSearch</B>, an intelligent
desktop-based search engine tool for browsers of the Web that significantly
improves the speed and accuracy of their searches. A simple, yet powerful
tool, <B>EchoSearch </B>is ideal for all users searching the Internet or a
corporate Intranet for information.
<P>

&quot;With the wealth of information available today online, millions of
users of the Internet and corporate Intranets need a tool to help sort
through and find relevant information,&quot; states Bernardo Sotomayor, vice
president and general manager of Iconovex.  &quot;<B>EchoSearch</B>
addresses the needs of those users, with a tool that will not only find
information, but synthesize and distill it.&quot;
<P>

Making use of Java's multi-threading capabilities, <B>EchoSearch</B> enables
users to simultaneously query multiple search engines.  Unlike other Web
search tools, <B>EchoSearch</B> features an intelligent back-end that can
index and accurately summarize the documents that are gathered in response
to the query.
<P>

Once the complete hit list has been built, <B>EchoSearch </B>again uses Java
's multi-threading capabilities to simultaneously download the documents AND
to process them linguistically, extracting the important phrases and ideas.
The resulting indexes and
summaries are then matched against the user's original query and the user is
presented with a condensed view that contains only the most relevant
entries.  These entries are then hyperlinked to their occurrences in the
original documents.
<P>

After viewing search results, a user has the option of refining the original
search by returning to the <B>EchoSearch </B>interface and clicking on the
&quot;<I>Refine Search</I>&quot; button. When this alternative is selected,
the program then displays another subset view of the refined query on the
initial global views (documents/hits that were found the first time).
<P>

&quot;Today's typical search engine is only capable of returning document
names and maybe the first sentence or two, thereby leaving end-users with
the time-consuming task of examining each hit individually,&quot; adds
Sotomayor. &quot;Our <B>EchoSearch </B>software takes searching to the
document content level by automatically collecting the summaries and indexes
that match the original query, thus improving both the speed and accuracy of
the search.&quot;
<P>

<B>EchoSearch </B>will be available July 1, 1996 for a suggested retail
price of  <B>$49.95</B>.  For additional information contact Iconovex
Corporation at 800-943-0292, on the Web at http://www.iconovex.com, or via
E-mail at fyi@iconovex.com.  EchoSearch joins the highly acknowledged
Iconovex product line, which includes <B>AnchorPage&#174;</B><B></B><B>,
WebAnchor&#153;</B><B></B>, <B>Indexicon&#174;</B><B></B>, and <B>SWAPI</B><B>&#153;</B>,<B> </B>
all of which are based on <B>Syntactica&#174;</B><B></B>, Iconovex's proprietary
indexing and abstracting engine.
<P>


<B><I>Iconovex Corporation is a software development company and a
wholly-owned subsidiary of Innovex, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive market.

<P>

</B></I>
