<P>

<B><EM>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</B></EM><B><I><EM>
<P>
<center><img src="TEMPBAR.GIF">
</B></I></EM><B>
<P>

<H2>ANNOUNCING WEBANCHOR</H2>


</B><B><I>Iconovex's Latest Addition to Its 
Suite of Organizational Tools</center>

<P>

</B></I>
<P>

<I>April 29, 1996 </I><I></I><I> </I>Bloomington, MN  <B>Iconovex
Corporation</B>, makers of software that understands ideas, has announced
the release of <B>WebAnchor</B>  an organizational tool that creates
hyperlinked back-of-the-book style indexes for RTF or HTML formatted
documents found on the World Wide Web, Local Area Networks, and your
desktop.  WebAnchor creates a personal Web of ideas for end-users, making it
easy to navigate through content-rich documents and access desired
information quickly.  For less than $50, users can quickly organize large
amounts of information within a hypertext environment.
<P>

WebAnchor analyzes RTF or HTML documents, generates an index that organizes
the information in those documents, and then automatically creates hypertext
links from the index to the original documents so that the information is
instantly accessible.  WebAnchor, which is based on Iconovex's proprietary
parsing technology, uses syntactical rules and semantic weight-in-context
not statistical analysis based on word frequency  to analyze written text
and extract the significant words, phrases and ideas.  The amount of
information contained in the index can be controlled through a simple Level
of Detail setting, making it possible to create fully detailed indexes for
individual documents or a high-level overview index of an entire Web site.

<P>


The big advantage WebAnchor offers is organization.  For the 10 million Web
browsers today, there is now a way to take HTML documents downloaded off the
Web, as well as documents on a personal computer, and organize them with an
index.  Instead of spending hours reading online, users can download
documents to their hard drive and let WebAnchor create a hyperlinked index
for quick and easy document navigation.
<P>

WebAnchor also offers advantages to Web developers, lessening the burden of
maintaining and linking information on both large and small web sites.  Web
site users will be able to jump directly from the familiar, intuitive form
of a back-of-the-book index to the source documents without having to
traverse intermediate menus or use a search engine with Boolean operators
and rules on capitalization to remember.  In addition, WebAnchor may also be
used to create a fully indexed and hyperlinked online help system.
<P>

&quot;We provide a fully automatic tool that will be indispensable for Web
users and developers,&quot; says Bart Davis, product marketing manager for
Iconovex.  &quot;WebAnchor creates an index from which the user can jump to
important terms and concepts in the source documents, saving valuable time.
&quot;
<P>

WebAnchor joins the Iconovex product line which includes <B>Syntactica&#174;
</B>,<B> </B>the
</B>proprietary indexing and summary engine which is the basis for <B>
Indexicon&#174;, </B>Iconovex's automatic indexing software for word
processors, and <B>AnchorPage&#174;</B>, the only automatic indexing,
summarizing, and hyperlinking software for corporate Intranets and External
Web sites.
<P>

WebAnchor is available through premier resellers and distributors with a s
uggested retail price of $49.95.  Direct orders can also be made by
contacting the Iconovex Corporation at (800) 943-0292, by email at fyi@
iconovex.com or on the Web at http://www.iconovex.com.  ICONOVEX Corporation
is a software development company and wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX,
Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's largest manufacturer of lead-wire
assemblies for the thin-film disk drive market.
<P>
<address><a href="mailto:cml@iconovex.com">webmaster</a></address>

