<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>New Syntactica API</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!-- RTFact 1.3 Iconovex Corporation 1995 -->

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
<pre><b>
						Contact:
						Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner
						EBS Public Relations, Inc.
						847-714-8600
</b></pre>
<P>

<B><EM>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</B></EM>
<center><img src="TEMPBAR.GIF">
<P>

<h2>NEW SYNTACTICA WEB API (SWAPI) FROM ICONOVEX CORP.</h2>
<P>

<B><I>Versatile, Easy-to-use API Enables Internet Software
Developers to <br>Quickly Create Web Applications</B></I></center>

<p>
<I>Bloomington, MN - </I>Iconovex Corporation, makers of software
that understands ideas, presents <B>Syntactica Web API (SWAPI)</B>, a
revolutionary technology that now enables Internet software developers to
prototype or develop new navigational tools in just a matter of days.
Featuring a very high level API that is based on Syntactica, Iconovex's
proprietary parsing and linguistic analysis engine, <B>SWAPI </B>is a
complete software development tool kit that offers developers unparalleled
ease-of-use and flexibility in creating both proof-of-concepts and complete
applications.
<P>

<B>SWAPI </B>is a C-language interface to a library that enables client
applications to perform linguistic analysis of HTML data and then
automatically hyperlink the various forms of linguistic output back to the
original source data. Hyperlinking is accomplished using standard HTML 2.0
conventions, and can be read by any HTML 2.0 compliant browser.  In
addition, <B>SWAPI </B>is capable of processing both ASCII and RTF file
formats.
<P>

&quot;<B>SWAPI </B>was developed so that software developers can create a
proof-of-concept within days instead of weeks or months,&quot; states Bart
Davis, product marketing manager for Iconovex.  '<B>SWAPI </B>will give
software developers the best tool available to automatically extract
significant phrases and ideas in their Internet/Intranet applications.&quot;

<P>


Four related, yet distinct linguistic outputs can be generated through <B>
SWAPI </B><B></B><B> </B>indexes, concepts, summary, and headings (table of
contents).  The developer's application can potentially request any
combination or all of the outputs simultaneously, and each output can be
adjusted individually for level of detail.
<P>

Indexes are the key words and phrases of the document in alphabetical order,
<I> not</I> a simple inverted word list. Concepts begin with the same
information as indexes (concept heads), and then expand that information to
offer a quick glimpse at the context in which the key words or phrases are
used (concept bodies).  The summary is a sequential presentation of the
significant ideas in a document rendered in the language of the original
text; headings provide a table of contents view of the document.
<P>

<B>SWAPI </B>also supports circular links, optional hypertext links that are
created within the source document that allow the browser to jump from one
instance of an index entry to the next instance of that index entry. Plus,
SWAPI Client Applications can operate in either File mode or Stream mode.
In File mode, the client specifies the HTML data as a set of files to be
processed and SWAPI supplies the processed data in set of files; in Stream
mode the client specifies the HTML data as a stream of bytes and SWAPI
supplies the processed data as a stream of bytes.
<P>

<B>SWAPI </B>is currently supported on Windows NT/95, Windows 3.x, Solaris
2.x, and Solaris 2.x for 80x86.  And, Macintosh support is planned for later
in 1996.

<P>

For additional <B>SWAPI</B> information or a price quotation, software
developers can contact Iconovex Corporation at 800-943-0292, or via E-mail
at fyi@iconovex.com.  SWAPI joins the highly acclaimed Iconovex product
line, which includes <B>AnchorPage</B><B></B><B> for Windows</B>, <B>
Syntactica</B><B></B>, the proprietary indexing engine which is the basis
for both SWAPI and the AnchorPage program, and <B>Indexicon</B><B></B>, the
only fully automatic indexing tool for word processors.
<P>


<B><I>Iconovex Corporation is a software development company and
wholly-owned subsidiary of Innovex, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive market.

<P>

</B></I>
<P>

