<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Price Reduction</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#0000FF" vlink="#663399">
<CENTER>
<H2>NEWS RELEASE</H2>
</CENTER>
<B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
<P><CENTER>
<i>ICONOVEX OFFERS HYPERTEXT INDEXING SOFTWARE FOR THE WEB AT A NEW LOWER 
PRICE </i></CENTER> <P>
<I></B>
	Bloomington, MN </I>--  ICONOVEX Corporation, leaders in automatic
	indexing and software, today announced it has lowered the price
	of its award winning <b>AnchorPage&#174;</b> software.  The new price
	of AnchorPage of $295, reduced from $895, offers a lower entry
	level price point for companies looking to organize the
	information found on their Web sites and corporate intranets by
	content.  AnchorPage is the only fully automatic hypertext
	indexing and abstracting software for use on Internet and
	corporate Webs.  This hypertext indexing is the foundation for
	<i><b>Content-Driven Navigation (CDN).</i></b>  Using CDN,
	users of a Web site will no longer have to aimlessly browse for
	information.  CDN provides a way for users to locate
	information, by content, quickly and easily and it increases
	the usability of that information.<p>  "With the tremendous
	expansion in the interest of the AnchorPage product and the
	idea of Content Driven Navigation, we have decided to lower the
	price of the software in order to increase its distribution,"
	says Bernardo Sotomayor, vice president and general manager of
	Iconovex.  "The lower price point will not only expand
	AnchorPage's market share, but also continue in increasing the
	acceptance of CDN as the standard for locating information both
	on the World Wide Web and internal corporate Web sites."<p>
	AnchorPage is unique in its use of true linguistic analysis to
	extract the significant phrases, concepts, and ideas from HTML
	documents.  By applying the rules of the English language and
	analyzing the individual words in their context, AnchorPage is
	able to "read" and understand HTML documents and provide
	concise synopses of the information contained within.  The
	software then automatically creates four different navigational
	views of the information (Table of Contents, Phrase, Concept,
	and Abstract Views).  These views are then hyperlinked from the
	index/abstract entry to its occurrence in the source text.<p>
	"AnchorPage is a true breakthrough in the way information will
	 be viewed on the Web," adds Sotomayor. "The current method of
finding information involves downloading and reading entire documents
on-line to find what you're searching for -- a very time consuming
chore.  A site that has been <b>AnchorPage'd</b> will provide visitors with
hyper-linked indexes of the relevant, significant phrases and concepts
from the information found at the site.  It is a content-driven search
of the site."  <p>Web site administrators decrease the system resources
	used by search engines while delivering content-rich
	information faster and easier.  They gain time savings by not
	having to manually read, index and abstract the text of their
	documents and then create all of the HTML tags.<p>  Included with
	AnchorPage are <B>RTFact&#153;</B> - a powerful RTF to HTML converter, and
	<b>LexEDIT&#153;</b> - a utility that allows users to customize the
	indexing output.  AnchorPage is available through premiere
	resellers and distributors, direct by contacting Iconovex
	Corporation at 800-943-0292, or by email at <A 
HREF="mailto:fyi@iconovex.com">fyi@iconovex.com</a>.
	You can also find both <a href="ANCHORPG.HTM">AnchorPage 
Demonstrations</a> and a <a href="/THEBEST.HTM">Listing of other sites 
using AnchorPage to their advantage</a>. AnchorPage joins the Iconovex 
product
	line, which includes <b>Syntactica&#174;</b>, the proprietary
	indexing engine which is the basis for the AnchorPage program
	and <b>Indexicon&#174;</b>, the only fully automatic indexing tool
	for word processors. <p> Iconovex Corporation is a software
	development company and wholly-owned subsidiary of Innovex,
	Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading manufacturer of
	lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive market.

