<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>NETSCAPE Selects Iconovex</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#0000FF" vlink="#663399">
<CENTER>
<H2>NEWS RELEASE</H2>
<IMG SRC="TEMPBAR.GIF" ALT=BAR><P></CENTER>
<B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
<P><CENTER>     
<i>ICONOVEX SELECTED BY NETSCAPE AND SUN MICROSYSTEMS 
TO PARTICIPATE IN INITIATIVE </i></CENTER>
<P>
<I>Hopkins, MN -- December 4, 1995 -- Innovex Inc.</I> (NASDAQ:  INVX) 
announced that its software division, Iconovex, has been selected by 
Netscape Communications Corporation (NASDAQ:  NSCP) and Sun Microsystems, 
Inc. (NASDAQ:  SUNW), to participate in its new industry initiative.  
JavaScript is an open, cross-platform object scripting language for the 
creation and customization of applications on enterprise networks and the 
Internet.  The JavaScript language complements Java&#153; Sun Microsystems' 
industry-leading object-oriented, secure cross-platform programming 
language.  The initial version of JavaScript and Java are available now as 
part of the Netscape Navigator&#153; 2.0 beta version, which is currently 
available for downloading from Netscape's website.  The draft specification 
of JavaScript, as well as the final draft specification of Java, is planned 
for publishing and submission to appropriate standards bodies for industry 
review and comment this month.
<P>

In addition to Iconovex, some of the other industry-leading companies who 
have agreed to adopt JavaScript and provide it in future products include 
IBM, AT&amp;T, Apple, Brio Technology, Inc., Digital Equipment Corporation, 
Hewlett-Packard Company, Illustra Information Technologies, Inc., Informix 
Software, Inc., Macromedia, Paper Software, Inc., Precept Software, RAD, 
Silicon Graphics, Inc. Sybase, Inc., Verity and Vermeer.
<P>

Innovex is the nation's leading manufacturer of lead wire assemblies for 
thin-film disk drives.  In addition to its disk drive business, Innovex also
manufactures various medical devices for OEM customers and software 
technology that automatically prepares indexes and abstracts of electronic 
documents.  The Company's common stock is traded on the National 
Over-the-Counter market under the NASDAQ symbol INVX.
<P>

