<html><head><title>AnchorPage for Windows 95/NT is now 
shipping</title></head><body><B>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</B><P>
<CENTER><H3>

ANCHORPAGE FOR  WINDOWS 95/NT IS NOW SHIPPING</CENTER></H3><BLOCKQUOTE>

        <I>Bloomington, MN -- October 20, 1995</I> --  ICONOVEX Corporation,
         leaders in automatic abstracting software, today began
         shipping AnchorPage for Windows 95/NT, the second title in a
         new line of software.  AnchorPage is the only fully automatic
         hypertext abstracting software for the World Wide Web.  This
         hypertext abstracting is the foundation for Content-Driven
         Navigation (CDN).  Using CDN, users of a Web site will no
         longer have to aimlessly browse for information.  CDN provides
         a way for users to locate information, by content, on the Web
         quickly and easily.  <p>AnchorPage is built from ICONOVEX's
        <b>Syntactica</b> engine that incorporates the semantic and
        syntactic rules of the English language to analyze HTML
        documents.  AnchorPage then extracts the significant phrases 
and concepts and automatically creates the HTML links from
        those phrases and concepts to their occurrences within the
        source document.  Finally, AnchorPage generates four
        Content-Driven Navigation views of the documents (Table of
        Contents, Abstract, Phrase, and Concept views).<p>  "AnchorPage is
         a true breakthrough in the way information will be viewed on
         the World Wide Web," states Robert Griggs, Vice President of
         Sales and Marketing for ICONOVEX.  "The current method of
         finding information involves downloading and reading the
         entire document(s) on-line to find what you're searching for
         -- a very time-consuming chore.  A site that has been
         AnchorPaged will provide visitors with hyper-linked indexes of
         the significant phrases and concepts from the information
         found at the site.  It is a content-driven search of that
         site."<p>

        Web site administrators gain time savings by not having to
        manually read, abstract and index the text of their documents
 and then create all of the HTML tags.  AnchorPage makes
        delivering information on the Web faster and more reliable.
        Included with AnchorPage are <b>RTFact</b>,  a powerful RTF to HTML
        converter, <b>LexEDIT</b>, a utility that allows users to customize
        the indexing process, and a Web browser to view the AnchorPage
        output.<p>  AnchorPage for Windows 95/NT and Windows 3.1x sells
        for $295 and is available through premiere resellers,
        distributors or <A HREF="ORDER.HTM">directly through Iconovex</a>. 
You can also contact ICONOVEX through <a 
href="mailto:fyi@iconovex.com">email</a>. AnchorPage 95/NT joins the 
ICONOVEX product 
line which includes Syntactica, the proprietary indexing engine which is 
the basis
        for the AnchorPage program, and <b>Indexicon</b>, the only fully
        automatic phrase indexing tool for word processors.  <p>ICONOVEX
        Corporation is a software development company and wholly-owned
        subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading
        manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk 
drive market.</BLOCKQUOTE> <p><pre>


Contact:                                    Contact:
Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner               Robert Griggs
EBS Public Relations                        ICONOVEX Corp.
708-714-8600                                VP of Sales and Marketing
                                            612-896-5109
</pre><p><hr><a href="/HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="ICONHOME.GIF"
