<html><head><title>AnchorPage Press Release</title></head><body>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                                           <p>

     <center><H3>INTERLEAF AND ICONOVEX ANNOUNCE TECHNOLOGY AND
     MARKETING PARTNERSHIP</H3></center>
<P><BLOCKQUOTE>
        <I>Bloomington, MN</I> -- Iconovex Corporation, the leader in
	automatic indexing software, and Interleaf, Inc., the leader in
	document management and publishing, have announced a technology
	partnership and a marketing agreement for all World Wide Web
	servers and for corporations using webs to distribute
	information internally.  The companies are working together,
	using complementary technologies to address the critical
	problem of building corporate webs and Internet World Wide Web
	sites that are well organized, manageable and easy to use.<p>
	The Interleaf-Iconovex partnership provides turn-key publishing
	solutions for all World Wide Web servers.  The companies are
	working together, using complementary technology to solve the
	problems of Internet publishing, navigation and information
	retrieval on the Web.  Interleaf's <b><i>Cyberleaf&#174;</i></b> and
     Iconovex's <b><i>AnchorPage&#153;</i></b> are two of the hottest
     products available in the fast-growing market for Web publishing
     and navigation software.<p>  Interleaf's product, Cyberleaf 1.0
     for UNIX, was released in February of 1995.  Cyberleaf is a
     software package that streamlines the process of publishing
     information on the World Wide Web.  It contains push-button
	technology that automatically transforms documents created with
	popular word processing applications into Internet-ready webs
	of information, without requiring users to learn tedious HTML
	code.  Cyberleaf goes beyond document conversion by also
	providing a complete Web production environment, including
	functionality for hyperlinking between various file types and
	for managing and updating multiple webs.<p>  Iconovex has
	recently introduced a new product called AnchorPage, the first
	title in a new line of software for the World Wide Web.
	AnchorPage is the only fully automatic hypertext indexing
	software for the Web.  This hypertext indexing is the
	foundation for <i><b>Content-Driven Navigation (CDN)</i></b>.
	Using CDN, users of a Web site will no longer have to aimlessly
	browse for information.  CDN provides a way for users to locate
	information, by content, on the Web quickly and easily.
	AnchorPage was the winner of a Byte Best of Comdex award in the
	Best New Development Software category at Spring Comdex 1995 in
	Atlanta, GA.  <p>
        "Enabling our customers to get the right information to the
	right person at the right time is our mission," says Bill
	Zoellick, director of business development at Interleaf.  "Web
	sites are an ideal way to do that, but only if they are a well
	structured publication rather than a collection of pages.  The
	combination of these two products allows customers to achieve
	that goal."    "<p>We feel that the partnership between
	Iconovex and Interleaf will be quite significant for all World
	Wide Web servers and people navigating the Web," adds Thomas
	Haley, Chairman and CEO of Innovex Corporation, Iconovex's
	parent company.  "We are collaborating to expand the reach of
	our resources, disseminate information on our technologies to
	the marketplace, and provide Web administrators with the best
	tools to create higher quality Web sites for the end user."
	<p>Cyberleaf is now available at a price of $1495 for Digital
	Equipment, Hewlett-Packard, IBM and Sun workstations.
	Cyberleaf 2.0 for Windows NT will be available during 1995.
	Cyberleaf is available through all distribution channels, VARs,
	Access Graphics and Merisel, direct from Interleaf by calling
	(800) 955-5323, or through email at i-direct@ileaf.com.
	<p>AnchorPage sells for $895 and is currently compatible with
	Windows. During the third quarter of 1995, Iconovex will
	release versions of AnchorPage for Solaris 2.4, Windows NT and
	Windows 95.  AnchorPage is available through premiere
	resellers, distributors or direct by contacting Iconovex
	Corporation at (800) 943-0292, or email at fyi@iconovex.com.
	<p>Interleaf (NASDAQ: LEAF), the leading worldwide supplier of
	document management solutions, provides a suite of software and
	services that automate information-intensive business
	processes.  Interleaf's integrated product line includes
	advanced software for electronic document preparation,
	publishing, management and distribution of business-critical
	information.  More information on <A HREF="http://www.ileaf.com">
Interleaf</a> and its complete
	line of powerful document management solutions can be found on
	the World Wide Web.<p>  Iconovex
	Corporation is a software development company and wholly-owned
	subsidiary of Innovex, Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX), the world's leading
	manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk
	drive market.  Further information on Iconovex's <a 
href="/PRODPAGE.HTM">complete line
	of automatic indexing solutions</A> can also be found on the World Wide
	Web.</BLOCKQUOTE> <p><pre>


Contact:                                    Contact:
Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner               Nora McGuinness
EBS Public Relations                        Interleaf, Inc.
708-714-8600	                            617-290-0710 x1325
