<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Resource Sites</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<H1><IMG SRC="WORLD.GIF" ALT="Globe"> Resource
Sites</h1><HR>These links lead to useful information about the Web and
Web-related subjects.
<P>
<ul> 
<LI><img src="NEW_TINY.GIF" alt="New!"><a 
href="http://www.keyscreen.com">Sander's Bestware Previewer</a><BR>
Our friend Sander in South Korea has a fine site that previews and 
reviews a number of popular shareware packages; he includes descriptions 
and screenshots.  Very helpful in evaluating shareware.
<LI><img src="NEW_TINY.GIF" alt="New!"><a 
href="http://www.serverwatch.com">Serverwatch</a> is a well-organized 
collection of links and information about web servers and many other 
aspects of web and internet technology and tools.  One of the hottest 
sites around (ok, so I'm a bit biased because they mention AnchorPage 
under "Hot Tools"/"Site Development - Management").
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pointcom.com/">Point Communication</a> reviews 
and <b>rates</b> thousands of the Web's top sites. They have quite an 
extensive "Internet" section with only the top 5% 
rated sites in each category making the grade enough to get listed on 
Point's site. This makes for a very useful 
site because they've "pre-browsed" the sites and offered their reviews so 
that you can take it from there. <p>
<LI><A HREF="http://WWW.Stars.com/Vlib">Web Developer's Virtual 
Library</a>; this is a comprehensive catalog with well over 1100 links 
to resources for Web development.<p><li><a 
href="http://www.cmpcmm.com/cc/companies.html">Computer & 
Communications Companies</a>; just what it sounds like -- a 
specialized, extensive list accessible through alphabetical listings 
as well as a search engine.<p>
<li><a href="http://techweb.cmp.com">TechWeb</a>; the "Technology 
Information Source".<p>
<li><a 
href="http://www.pulver.com:80/netwatch/">NetWatch</a>..."Perspectives 
on Enabling Technologies"<p><li><a 
href="http://union.ncsa.uiuc.edu/HyperNews/get/hypernews.html">HyperNews</a>; 
a cross between the hypermedia of the Web and Usenet News.<p><li><a 
href="http://www.aeiveos.com/">Aeiveos Home Page</a>; scrolling 
down this homepage one will find a "WWW Information, documentation and 
pointers" section.<p><li><a href="http://www-swiss.ai.mit.edu/wtr/">Web 
Tools Review Page</a>; an online journal for developers of WWW sites.<p> 
<li><a href="http://www.mecklerweb.com/mags/ww/wwhome.htm"><cite>Web
Week</cite></a>, Mecklermedia's new publication, has a wealth of
information and current web-happenings; this is a good place to
check out on a regular basis especially because from their <a
href="http://www.mecklerweb.com">MecklerWeb home page</a> you
can access <a 
href="http://www.mecklerweb.com/mags/iw/iwhome.htm"><cite>Internet
World</cite></a> and a host of other information<P>
<li><a href="http://www.mcp.com">Macmillan USA Information Super
Library(tm).</a> Macmillan Press' homepage and home of the <a
href="http://www.mcp.com/nrp/wwwyp">World Wide Web Yellow Pages.</a>
In addition to Macmillan's on-line catalogue for ordering books, you
can find shareware and some decent links here<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tncnet.com"><IMG SRC="VNSLOGO.GIF" 
ALT="Visicom"> Visicom Network Systems</a>; <b>"The Network 
Connection"</b> Internet Service Provider to the Business Community,
is establishing a network of clients, suppliers and
sales & marketing resources. Visit their site to see
how their resources can help you establish your
Internet presence.
<li><A 
HREF="http://www.mitsi.com"><img src="MTSI.GIF" ALT="MTSI">MTSI (Micro 
Technology Services Inc.)</a> are authorized Motorola System Integrators 
for the entire line of Motorola VME and PowerPC(tm) Products.</ul><P><HR><A 
HREF="HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG 
SRC="ICONHOME.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="Return"> Return to the Iconovex 
HomePage</a><p><address>February 5, 
1997&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;cml@iconovex.com</address></body></html>
