<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Installation  Instructions</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#663399">
<H2 align=center><IMG SRC="ANCHOR.GIF" ALT="AnchorPage logo">
AnchorPage<SUP>&#174;</SUP> Installation Instructions</H2>

<BR><BR>
<center>
<a href="#sysreq">System Requirements</a> &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#install">Installation Instructions</a>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#remove">Removing the Demo</a>
</center>

<BR><BR><B>This version of AnchorPage is a limited demonstration copy.</b>
You may process up to 50,000 Bytes (50K) of source files, which equates to
roughly 25 pages of HTML documents, depending on the density of the text.  If
you exceed the 50K and would like to continue to process on smaller
documents, you must reset AnchorPage by exiting the program and then
restarting it.
<P><b>Not included in this evaluation copy of AnchorPage</b> are
two utilities that ship with the full version: <A
HREF="/RTFACT.HTM">RTFact</A>, an RTF  to HTML converter, and <A
HREF="/LEXEDIT.HTM">LexEdit</A>, a customizing lexicon utility.

<br><BR><a name="sysreq"></a>
<h2>System Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>486 Processor or better
<li>Microsoft  Windows 3.1x, WFW 3.1x, Windows 95, or Windows NT
<li>8MB RAM (Windows 3.1x, WFW 3.1x, & Windows 95)--16 MB RAM (Windows NT)
<li>Documents in RTF or HTML format
<li>Win32s 1.30x (Windows 3.1 users only).  For more information see our
<a href="../../TECHSUPP.HTM#Win32s">Technical Support area</a>
</ul>


<a name="install"></a>
<h2>Installation Instructions</h2>

<P> <A
HREF="#WIN31NT">Anchorpage for Windows&#160;3.1 or
Windows&#160;NT</A> <BR>
<A HREF="#WIN95">Anchorpage for Windows 95</A>

<P><A NAME="WIN31NT">
<H3>Anchorpage for Windows&#160;3.1 or
Windows&#160;NT</H3>

<OL>
<li> Download the file "ancreval.exe" into an empty directory.
<li>From the Program or File Manager, choose RUN.
<li>In the text box, enter <B>c:\{directory}\ancreval.exe</B> (where
{directory} is the directory to which you have downloaded the file
"ancreval").  This will unpack the archived file and create, among
other things, a program called "setup.exe."
<li>Using the same method as in steps 2 and 3, run <b>setup.exe</b> from
the directory where you unpacked ancreval.exe.

</LI>
<LI>	IMPORTANT:  You will be presented with a copy of the AnchorPage 	Limited
Evaluation License Agreement.  By installing AnchorPage, you agree to the
terms and conditions of the agreement.  This file can also be viewed in
the c:\temp directory as 'evalicns.txt.'
</LI>
<LI>	Once you have read the agreement and agree to the terms and
conditions, you must close the Notepad containing the License Agreement
before continuing with the installation.
</LI>
<LI>    At the next screen, choose INSTALL.
</LI>
<LI>    Follow the instructions on the screen and indicate the appropriate
        operating system you are using.
</LI>
<LI>    Please review the APREADME.TXT file for any last minute changes or
	updates to AnchorPage.
</LI>
</OL>

<P> <A NAME="WIN95">
<H3>Anchorpage for Windows 95</H3> </A>
<OL>
<li> Download the file "ancreval.exe" into an empty directory.
<LI>Click the START button.</LI>
<LI>     From the pop-up menu, click RUN.
<li>In the text box, enter <B>c:\{directory}\ancreval.exe</B> (where
{directory} is the directory to which you have downloaded the file
"ancreval").  This will unpack the archived file and create, among
other things, a program called "setup.exe."
<li>Using the same method as in steps 2 and 3, run <b>setup.exe</b> from
the directory where you unpacked ancreval.exe.

</LI>
<LI>	IMPORTANT:  You will be presented with a copy of the AnchorPage 	Limited
Evaluation License Agreement.  By installing AnchorPage, you 	agree to the terms
and conditions of the agreement.  This file can 	also be viewed in the d:\icon
directory as 'evalicns.txt'.
</LI>
<LI>	Once you have read the agreement and agree to the terms and 	conditions,
you must close the Notepad containing the License 	Agreement before continuing
with the installation.
</LI>
<LI>    At the next screen, choose INSTALL.
</LI>
<LI>	Follow the instructions on the screen and indicate the appropriate
        operating system you are using.
</LI>
<LI>	Please review the APREADME.TXT file for any last minute changes or
	updates to AnchorPage.
</LI>
</OL>

<a name="remove">
<h2>How to Remove the Demo </h2>

All program files installed with AnchorPage are saved in the
directory where you chose to install AnchorPage.  To remove AnchorPage from
your system, simply delete that directory.
<BR><BR>
