<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>The Net Magazine Review</title></head><body>
<h1>The Net</h1><hr> 
<blockquote><I>Taken from "Blue Grrl's"
review found in the September 1995 issue of 
<B>The Net</B></i><UL><h2>software/<br>hardware</h2><p>&#160;&#160;..As we 
noted then 
(August issue of "The Net"), AnchorPage-built sites let those who 
log onto them search for what they're looking for and quickly find it. 
Now, after I've subjected it to a full-fledged test, I have to say that 
AnchorPage delivers on its promise (and I was even using a beta 
version).<br>&#160;&#160;<B>Yes it's amazing. Revolutionary. Extraordinary. 
Exceptional. If you run a Web site that's fat with text-based 
information, you absolutely need to write out a check for $895. Now. I 
kid you not.</B><br>&#160;&#160;O.K., so what does this miracle software do? 
It reads a document, analyzes the test by sorting which items (you can 
control these values) are most significant, and then creates a table of 
comtents, a "concept" page, and an "abstract." Amazingly enough, it 
works. It's also fully automatic; fast (300 words per second); and gives 
you the power to customize priorities.<BR>. . .<BR>&#160;&#160;The program 
seemed a 
bit menacing to me at first, but a brief look at the manual and a little 
trial and error got me off and running pretty quickly. The software comes 
with some samples, which are also found at the Web site, I recommend that 
you take a long, hard look at these samples; they'll help you understand 
the concept much faster than any manual could. Also, Iconovex is so sure 
of its product that if you send in an HTML or RTF document via disk or 
e-mail, it will run it through AnchorPage and send it back to you, fully 
indexed, so you'll see first hand the miracles of this intelligent 
document handling. Give it a whirl. It is worth it. 
<b>A</B><sup>*</sup><p>(emphasis added -- 
ed.)<p>--BG<P>* For a summary of "The Net's" review 
procedures and rating system you can visit <A 
HREF="http://www.thenet-usa.com/">their 
site</a><HR></BLOCKQUOTE></ul><p><B>You can also see <i>The Net</i>'s <a 
href="http://www.thenet-usa.com/mag/back/0995/hs.html#anchor">online 
review of AnchorPage</a></B><p><hr><a href="/HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG 
SRC="ICONHOME.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="Return"> Return to the Iconovex 
HomePage</a><p><address>November 28th, 1995 
cml@iconovex.com</address></body></html>
