<html><head><title>AnchorPage Reseller Week Review</title></head><body>
<H1>Reseller Week</h1><hr>NEWS FOR THE COMPUTER RESELLER FROM COMPUTER 
RESELLER LABS<HR><BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>HOT FROM THE 
LABS&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; 
July 3, 1995</h3> <ul><STRONG>Breakthrough Technologies:</STRONG><BR>By Ken 
Yamada<br>San Mateo, Calif.<hr>Information on the Internet typically 
becomes useful to people only after they find the appropriate document, 
then within it, find the desired data. Iconovex Corp. has begun shipping 
a software tool that purports to solve at least part of that challenge.<br>
&#160;&#160;<b>Resellers interested in providing solutions for the 
Internet's World Wide Web should be sure that a copy of AnchorPage is 
close at hand. This product is clever and useful.</b><br>&#160;&#160;
The company's AnchorPage software categorizes and indexes text documents 
for use on the World Wide Web. According to the company, the software 
relies on its ability to recognize and understand words and phrases in 
context, then automatically creates lists of those words and builds 
hyperlinks to the exact location in the text where they can be 
found.<br><b>. . .</b><BR>(emphasis added --ed.)</ul>*Excerpted with 
permission from <b>Reseller Week</b> July 3rd issue</blockquote> <hr> <A 
HREF="/HOMEPAGE.HTM"><IMG SRC="ICONHOME.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE
ALT="Return"> Return to the Iconovex HomePage</a><p><address>September 13th,
1995 cml@iconovex.com</address></body></html>
