<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Press Release</title></head><body> 
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<P><CENTER>
<H3>ANCHORPAGE&#153; FOR WINDOWS RELEASED; WINDOWS NT, WINDOWS 95,
AND SOLARIS 2.4 (UNIX) VERSIONS ANNOUNCED</H3></CENTER><P>
<I>Bloomington, MN -- July 7, 1995 --</I>  ICONOVEX Corporation, leaders in
automatic indexing software, today began shipping <B>AnchorPage</B>, the
first title in a new line of software for the World Wide Web.  AnchorPage is
the only fully automatic hypertext indexing software for the World Wide Web.
This hypertext indexing is the foundation for <B><I>Content-Driven
Navigation </B></I><B>(CDN)</B><B><I>.  </B></I>Using CDN, users of a Web
site will no longer have to aimlessly browse for information.  CDN provides
a way for users to locate information, by content, on the Web quickly and
easily.<P>AnchorPage is built from ICONOVEX's <A 
HREF="/SYNTAC.HTM"><B>Syntactica&#174;</B>
engine</A> that incorporates the linguistic, semantic and syntactic rules 
of the
English language to &quot;read&quot; HTML documents.  AnchorPage then
extracts the significant phrases and concepts and automatically creates the
HTML links from those phrases and concepts to their occurrences within the
source document.  Finally, AnchorPage generates four <I>Content-Driven
Navigation</I> views of the documents (Table of Contents, Abstract, Phrase,
and Concept views). 
<P>&quot;AnchorPage is a true breakthrough in the way information will be
viewed on the World Wide Web,&quot; states Robert Griggs, Vice President of
Sales and Marketing for ICONOVEX.  &quot;The current method of finding
information involves downloading and reading the entire document(s) on-line
to find what you're searching for -- a very time-consuming chore.  A site
that has been <B>AnchorPaged</B> will provide visitors with hyperlinked
indexes of the significant phrases and concepts from the information found
at the site.  It is a content-driven search of that site.&quot;
<P>Web site administrators gain time savings by not having to manually read,
index and abstract the text of their documents and then create all of the
HTML tags.  AnchorPage makes delivering information on the Web faster and
more reliable.<P> During the 3rd quarter of 1995, <A 
HREF="/ICONOVEX.HTM">ICONOVEX</A> will release
AnchorPage for Solaris 2.4 (UNIX), Windows NT and the new Windows '95
operating system platforms. With the great response and acceptance of the
AnchorPage technology, this broadening of the platform base will continue
the accelerated growth of AnchorPage.<P> Included with AnchorPage are
<A 
HREF="/AP.HTM#RTFACT"><B>RTFact&#153;</B></A> 
- a powerful RTF to HTML converter,
<A HREF="/LEXEDIT.HTM"><B>LexEDIT&#153;</B></A> - a utility that allows 
users to customize the
indexing output and generate a list of &quot;unknown&quot; words not
recognized by AnchorPage, and <B>Netscape Navigator 1.0</B> - to view the
AnchorPage output.<P> AnchorPage sells for $295 and is available through
<a href="http://www.iconovex.com/ANCHOR/ORDER.HTM">premiere resellers, 
distributors or direct</A> by 
calling ICONOVEX Corporation at 800-943-0292, through email at <A 
HREF="mailto:fyi@iconovex.com">fyi@iconovex.com</a>, or 
test drive some <a 
href="http://www.iconovex.com/ANCHOR/DEMOS.HTM">AnchorPage 
demonstrations</A> on the World Wide Web.
AnchorPage joins the ICONOVEX product line, which includes <A 
HREF="/SYNTAC.HTM">Syntactica</A>,
the proprietary indexing engine which is the basis for the AnchorPage
program and <A HREF="/INDEX.HTM"><B>Indexicon</B></A>, the only fully 
automatic indexing tool for
word processors. <P> ICONOVEX Corporation is a software development
company and wholly-owned subsidiary of <A HREF="/INNOVEX.HTM">INNOVEX, 
Inc.</A> (NASDAQ: INVX), the
world's leading manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film
disk drive market. <P><PRE>
Contact:                          Contact:

Erica Swerdlow/Craig Grabiner     Robert Griggs
EBS Public Relations              Vice President Sales & Marketing
708-714-8600                      Iconovex Corporation
                                  612-896-5109
                                              </pre>
