<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Innovex Press Release #4</title></head><body>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE

<CENTER><H3>INNOVEX JOINS FORCES WITH JDL TECHNOLOGIES TO DISTRIBUTE AWARD
        WINNING ANCHORPAGE SOFTWARE</H3></CENTER>

August 4, 1995--Hopkins, MN--Innovex Inc. (NASDAQ: INVX) today announced
that its wholly-owned subsidiary, Iconovex, has reached an agreement with
JDL Technologies, Inc., whereby JDL Technologies will be the sole distributor
of Innovex's AnchorPage technology to the K-12 education market.
        <p>
JDL Technologies provides sophisticated and affordable networking and
Internet solutions exclusively to the education market and is the
exclusive distributor of such products as Netscape Communications
products for the education market.
        <p>
AnchorPage, the first title in a new
line of software for the World Wide Web, is the only fully automatic
hyperlinking and indexing software for the World Wide Web.  This hypertext
indexing is the foundation for Content-Driven Navigation (CDN).  Using
CDN, users of a Web site will no longer have to aimlessly browse for
information.  CDN provides a way for users to locate information, by
content, on the Web quickly and easily.  AnchorPage was the winner of
Byte Magazine's Best of Comdex Award for Best New Development Software at
Spring Comdex in April, 1995.
        <p>  "This product is a very powerful, robust
tool for educators to use in creating and maintaining World Wide Web
sites for their schools," says Tom Lapping, President of JDL
Technologies.  "When AnchorPage is used in conjunction with products like
the Netscape server software, educators can provide their colleagues with
secure, instantaneous, rich environments on the Web.  We are excited
about working with individual schools and
school districts and helping them solve their document access problems
with this breakthrough product."
        <p>During the third quarter of 1995,
Iconovex will release AnchorPage for Solaris 2.4 (UNIX), Windows NT and
the new Windows '95 operating system platforms.  With the great response 
and acceptance of the AnchorPage technology, this broadening of the
platform base will continue the accelerated growth of AnchorPage.
<p>AnchorPage is a Windows application that requires Microsoft Windows 
3.1 or
Windows for Workgroups 3.1 or later.  It processes HTML documents and
requires 8 MB of RAM to function efficiently.

