<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Press Release</title></head><body> 
<center><B>AnchorPage</b></center><p>FOR IMMEDIATE 
RELEASE<center><h3>ANNOUNCING JOINT
TECHNOLOGY PARTNERSHIP WITH CORNERSTONE IMAGING, INC.</h3></center><P>
Bloomington, MN.  ICONOVEX Corporation, the leader in automatic
indexing software, announces the integration of its Syntactica
technology into Cornerstone Imaging's powerful Input<I>Accel</i> technology
platform.  Iconovex joins a large group of providers of technology
to this open integration platform used in the document capture
process.<P>
 The Input<I>Accel</I> process is an open integration platform
for the peripherals, engines, and products used in the document
capture process, including image enhancement engines, OCR/ICR
engines, data entry technologies and now <B>Syntactica</B>.  Because
Input<I>Accel</I> provides a straightforward way to connect these
technologies, it is now easier for System Integrators to develop
production document capture systems.  The Input<I>Accel</I> platform
also provides a standardized interface that image-enabled application
developers can use to easily add new document capture functions
to their products.<P>
 With the integration of Syntactica's textual analysis of documents 
processed by Input <I>Accel</I>, the information in a document
or documents is now automatically and electronically indexed,
concept-indexed, and abstracted. The text is transformed into
intelligent and  referenceable documents with the information
contained organized internally, identified, and made retrievable
like never before.<P>
 Syntactica's fast conceptual analysis of text documents, up to
300 words per second, produces any or all of the three outputs:
Concept, Abstract and Phrase indexes.  Syntactica breaks text
down into phrases, using semantic and syntactic analysis to rank
the phrases and produce indexes at the level of detail specified
by the user.<P>
 Syntactica's semantic decisions are based on an extensive lexicon,
or word list.  Specialty lexicons, such as a legal lexicon, can
also be added to enhance the output when processing technical
documents.<P>
 With the joining of these technologies, both companies see user
benefits that will accelerate the implementation and acceptance
of this unique and open platform.
<P>
 Cornerstone Imaging, Inc. is the technology and market leader
in document imaging display products and has recently announced
the Input<i>Accel</i> document capture product.  Cornerstone Imaging,
Inc. is a publicly held company traded on the NASDAQ National
Market under the symbol CRNR.<P>
 ICONOVEX Corporation is a software development company and a
wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive
market.
<p>
<pre>
Contact:
Robert Griggs                           Nancy McCluskey-Moore
Vice President Sales and Marketing      Marketing Communications Manager
Iconovex Corporation                    Cornerstone Imaging, Inc.
612-896-5109                            408-434-3318
</pre>    
