<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Press Release</title></head><body> 
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<P>
<center><h3>ICONOVEX'S ANCHORPAGE WINS BYTE'S "BEST OF COMDEX"
AWARD</h3></center> <P>
 Atlanta, GA, April 26, 1995.  Byte Magazine announced Iconovex
Corporation as the winner of the 1995 Best of Comdex/Spring Award
in the category of  Best Development Software for their new software
program, AnchorPage.<P>
 The AnchorPage program extracts the significant phrases and concepts
from either a single World Wide Web document or a collection of
such documents and automatically inserts hypertext anchors for
each of these phrases and concepts.  Its fast conceptual analysis
of HTML documents produces any or all of four synopses: Concept,
Abstract and Phrase Pages, as well as a Table of Contents Page.
 The entries within these synopsis pages become &quot;hot words&quot;
with automatic links to the passages in the documents from which
they were generated.  This allows readers to quickly and easily
skim any of the AnchorPage-generated synopses for items of interest
and to call up the pertinent document with the click of a mouse.
<P> &quot;We are very excited that AnchorPage was recognized for
its innovative technology by such a distinguished, highly regarded
publication, &quot; says Robert Griggs, Vice President of Sales
and Marketing for Iconovex.<P> Byte's &quot;Best of Comdex&quot; awards
program is a time-honored tradition in the computer industry after seven
years of presentations.  In evaluating products, Byte editors seek out
innovative new products that show strong potential to influence and
impact the computer industry worldwide.<P>
 &quot;We have a really strong core development group that has
worked together on this project since its inception,&quot; states
Bernardo Sotomayor, Vice President and General Manager of Iconovex.
&quot;That close team effort has just begun to pay off with 
AnchorPage.&quot;<P>
 AnchorPage sells for $295 and is available through a select group
of resellers and integrators.  It can be ordered direct by calling
Iconovex Corporation at 800-943-0292, through e-mail at Compuserve 74064,440
and FYI@iconovex.com or by accessing their Web site at 
http://www.iconovex.com.
Sales, technical inquiries and product information requests may be directed
to the above numbers or to Iconovex Corporation at 7900 Xerxes Ave.
South, Suite 550, Bloomington, MN  55431.
<P> AnchorPage joins the ICONOVEX product line which includes Syntactica,
Indexicon, and LexEdit. Syntactica's linguistic analysis is the
basis for the AnchorPage program and its core technology is available
for developers in an API.  Indexicon is Iconovex's automatic indexing
software program for word processors, and  LexEdit is an add-on
tool that allows users to create personal word lists for all of
Iconovex's programs.
<P> Iconovex Corporation is a software development company and a
wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive
market.
<p>
