<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>AnchorPage Press Release</title></head><body> 
<center><b>AnchorPage</b></center><p>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
<center><h3>ICONOVEX ANNOUNCES FULL PRODUCT COMPATIBILITY WITH NETSCAPE
COMMUNICATIONS</h3></center> <P>
Bloomington, MN.  ICONOVEX Corporation, the leader in automatic
indexing software, announces the compatibility of <B>AnchorPage</B>,
an automatic hypertext anchoring program which inserts HTML tags
into document databases for the World Wide Web, with Netscape
Communication's Mosaic Netsite Communications Server and the Mosaic
Netsite Commerce Server.<P>
 ICONOVEX and Netscape Communications are committed to providing
the highest level of integration of their respective technologies,
thus bringing the greatest amount of service, performance and
utilization to WWW servers who are using Netsite server software
and AnchorPage.<P>
 AnchorPage's fast conceptual analysis of text documents produces
any or all of four synopses: Concept, Abstract and Phrase Pages, as well
as a Table of Contents Page.  The entries within these synopsis
pages become &quot;hot words&quot; with automatic links to the
passages in the documents from which they were generated.  This 
hypertext linkage allows a reader to quickly skim any of the
AnchorPage-generated synopses for items of interest and to call up the
pertinent document with the click of a mouse.<P>
 &quot;AnchorPage is a true breakthrough
in the way information is found on and accessed from Web servers,&quot;
states Robert Griggs, Vice President of Sales and Marketing for
Iconovex. &quot;The current method involves manual insertion of
HTML tags on the part of a server administrator to create hypertext
links.  Because of time constraints and the increasing volume
of information posted on servers, most documents have links only
to their titles.  AnchorPage links you to the key phrases and
concepts within those documents.&quot;<P>
 AnchorPage makes retrieving information on the World Wide Web
faster and more reliable.  Once a Web site uses AnchorPage to
link all of its documents, users of that Web site will be able
to view synopsis pages of the documents they think may be relevant
to their search, retrieving them in a fraction of the time it
would take to download the entire document.  They can scan the
phrases, concepts, abstracts or table of contents for relevant
information, and upon finding it, click on the appropriate entry
and retrieve the section of the document from which the entry was
generated.<P>
&quot;AnchorPage's real-time HTML tag generation allows publishers
to post documents faster while reducing administration costs,&quot;
states Griggs.  &quot;Easy access to the most recent information
will make any Web site more profitable.&quot;<P>
 Anchor Page is a Windows application that requires Microsoft
Windows 3.1 or Windows for Workgroups 3.1 or later.  It fully
automates concept extraction and hypertext anchoring of HTML documents
and requires 8 MB of RAM to function efficiently.  It can create
hypertext links between documents (as between a home page and
a document) or between related entries within a document.  The
user can select multiple documents to process at once and can
choose any or all four possible outputs:  Table of contents, Phrase
page, Concept page, and Abstract page.  These four output forms
can also be horizontally linked such that an entry in the phrase
page can contain a hypertext link to the related concept entry,
which can also be linked to the related abstract entry.  This  
gives Web servers a full set of options in designing the access
and entry points to the documents in their database.<P>
 AnchorPage joins the ICONOVEX product line which includes Syntactica,
the core technology, available for developers in an API. Syntactica's
linguistic analysis is the basis for the AnchorPage program. Indexicon
is ICONOVEX's  automatic indexing software program for word processors,
and finally LexEdit, an add on tool that allows users to create
personal word lists for Indexicon.<P>
AnchorPage sells for $895 and is available direct by calling
ICONOVEX Corporation at 800-943-0292, accessing their Web site
at <strong>http://www.iconovex.com</strong>, or through e-mail at 
Compuserve 74$
Technical inquiries and product information requests may be
directed to the above numbers or to  ICONOVEX Corporation at
7900 Xerxes Ave. South, Suite 550, Bloomington, MN 55431.<P>
 Netscape Communications Corporation is a premier provider of
open software to enable people and companies to exchange information
and conduct commerce over the Internet and other global networks.
The company was founded in April 1994 by Dr. James H. Clark, founder
of Silicon Graphics, Inc., a Fortune 500 computer systems company;
and Marc Andreessen, creator of the NCSA Mosaic research prototype
for the Internet. Privately held, Netscape Communications Corporation
is based in Mountain View, California.
<P>
ICONOVEX Corporation is a software development company and a
wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive
market.
<p>

