<hr>
After
you hit <b><i>Search</b></i>, EchoSearch will send your request to seven
search engines simultaneously and begin returning successful result until it
reaches the number that you requested.  When you submit an advanced query,
EchoSearch will only submit your query to the search engines that support
such queries. This insures a more relevant document set.  Lycos and
Webcrawler, shown on the screen below as "Unsupported," do not allow the
"must include" operator. <p>

