<HEAD>
<TITLE>EchoSearch Sample Output #1(2-B)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="SPOTS.GIF">
<hr>
Choosing <b><i>Options  Search Engines</b></i> on EchoSearch's main
screen will bring up the dialog shown below.  All of the search engines used
by EchoSearch are listed here. You can select or deselect any of the search
engines for any particular query.  We have selected to obtain hits based
on <i>speed</i> (fastest return) rather than on <i>relevance</i> (equal number
of hits from each search engine).  On this screen, you can designate how
often you would like EchoSearch to automatically check for, and download as
necessary, new search engine drivers from our Web site, to keep your copy of
EchoSeach up-to-date. You can also choose whether or not to view the hit list
(list of URLs returned by the search engines) before downloading.<p>
