<html>
<body bgcolor="FFCC99">
<TITLE>Search Engine Clones</TITLE>

<h1 align=center>Search Engine Clones</h1>

<hr>
<p>
<P>Some search engines are available in different versions for different
areas of the world or even "Intranet" versions that can reside on your
internal network.  You can use the clone feature to add another version of
a search engine type supported by EchoSearch, for example, an Intranet or
European version of a search engine.  Included here are:
<P>
<ul>
<li>instructions for <a href="#updating">updating</a> the search engine list,
<li>information for the <a href="#supported">clones supported</a> by
EchoSearch, including the URLs that need to be included in the settings for
each clone,
<li>and clones that will be <a href="#added">added</a> to future releases of
EchoSearch. </ul>
<P>

<a name="updating"></a>
<h3>How to Update Your Search Engine List</h3>
<p>If any of the
supported clones are not listed in your search engine list (on the Search
Engines dialog), you can obtain updates and additions to the list online:
<P><ol>
  <Li>Open your Internet connection if it is not already open.
  <li>Open <b>Options - Search Engines</b>.
  <li>Click <b>Update Now</b>.
  <li>When the update is complete, click <b>OK</b>.
  <br>EchoSearch will automatically update any existing search engine drivers
  and add any new drivers.
</ol>

<h3>How to Request That a Search Engine or Search Engine Clone Be Added to
EchoSearch</h3>
<P> If a Search Engine Type (e.g., AltaVista, Infoseek, Excite) or
Search Engine Clone (e.g., AltaVista Australia) is not included in the list
of <a href="#supported">supported clones</a> or is not in the list of <a
href="#added">search engines and clones to be added</a> to EchoSearch, you
can send us a request using the <a href="SENGINE.HTM">Search Engine Request
form</a>.

<BR><BR><BR>

<a name="supported"></a>
<P><h3>Clones Supported by and Included in
EchoSearch</h3> <P>

<table cellpadding=5 border=1 cols=3> <tr> <td colstart=1
colspan=3><b>Search Engine Type</b></td> </tr> <tr> <td
