<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>System Requirements and Installation Instructions for WebAnchor</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<h2 align=center>System Requirements and Installation Instructions for
WebAnchor1.0</h2>

<BR><BR>
<center>
<a href="#sysreq">System Requirements</a> &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#install">Installation Instructions</a>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
<a href="#remove">Removing the Demo</a>
</center>

<BR><BR>
This version of WebAnchor(TM) is a limited demonstration copy.  You may
process up to 30,000 Bytes (30K) of source files, which equates to roughly 10
pages of HTML documents, depending on the density of the text.  If you
exceed the 30K limit and would like to continue to process on smaller
documents, you must reset WebAnchor by exiting the program and then
restarting it.

<BR>
<a name="sysreq"></a>
<h2>System Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>Windows 3.1x, Windows 95, or Windows NT 3.51<p>
<li>486 or better CPU<p>
<li>8 MB RAM (Windows 3.1x, Windows 95)--16 MB RAM (Windows NT)<p>
<li>Win32s 1.30x (Windows 3.1 users only).  For more information see our
<a href="../../TECHSUPP.HTM#Win32s">Technical Support area</a> <p>
</ul>


<a name="install"></a>
<h2>Installation Instructions</h2>

<h3>WebAnchor for Windows 3.1 (or later) and Windows NT:</h3>
<p>
<blockquote>
	1. Download the file "webanchor.exe" to an empty directory.
<p>
	2. From the Program or File Manager, choose RUN.
<p>
        3. In the text box, enter <B>c:\{directory}\webanch.exe</B> (where
{directory} is the directory to which you have downloaded the file
"webanch.exe").  This will unpack the archived file and create, among
other things, a program called "setup.exe."
<p>
	4.  Using the same method as in steps 2 and 3, run <b>setup.exe</b> from
the directory where you unpacked webanchor.exe.
 <p>
        5.  IMPORTANT:  You will be presented with a copy of the WebAnchor
        Limited Evaluation License Agreement.  By installing WebAnchor, you
        agree to the terms and conditions of the agreement.
<p>
	6. Once you have read the agreement and agree to the terms and
	conditions, you must close the Notepad containing the License
	Agreement before continuing with the installation.
<p>
	7. At the next screen, choose INSTALL.
<p>
        8. Please review the README.TXT file for any last minute changes or
        updates to WebAnchor.
<p>
</blockquote>


<h3>WebAnchor for Windows 95:</h4>
<blockquote>
	1. Download the file "webanchor.exe" to an empty folder/directory.
<p>
	2. Click the START button.
<p>
	3. From the pop-up menu, click RUN.
<p>
        4. In the text box enter <B>c:\{directory}\webanch.exe</B> (where
{directory} is the directory to which you have downloaded the file
"webanch.exe").
<p>
	5.  Using the same method as in steps 3 and 4,
run <b>setup.exe</b> from the directory where you unpacked webanchor.exe.
<p>
        6.  IMPORTANT:  You will be presented with a copy of the WebAnchor
        Limited Evaluation License Agreement.  By installing WebAnchor, you
        agree to the terms and conditions of the agreement.
<p>
	7. Once you have read the agreement and agree to the terms and
	conditions, you must close the Notepad containing the License
	Agreement before continuing with the installation.
<p>
	8. At the next screen, choose INSTALL.
<p>
        9. Please review the README.TXT file for any last minute changes or
        updates to WebAnchor.
</blockquote>


<a name="remove">
<h2>How to Remove the Demo </h2>

All program files installed with WebAnchor are saved in the
directory where you chose to install WebAnchor.  To remove WebAnchor from
your system, simply delete that directory.

