<TITLE>The Iconovex Corporation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>


<p>
<U>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</U>
<P>
<center><h3>NEW TEXT PROCESSING TECHNOLOGY AUTOMATES THE PROCESS OF INDEXING AND ABSTRACTING</h3></center>
<P>
Bloomington, MN.   The ICONOVEX Corporation introduces <strong>Syntactica</strong>
-- an automatic indexing system that understands the subtleties
of the English language. This new indexing tool kit can locate
the significant terms and concepts in a document and present the
user with a list which displays those terms and concepts as they
appear in context.
<P>
 &quot;Personal computers, modems, and networks have brought business
into the Information Age.  Unfortunately, most businesses are
simply overwhelmed by the huge volume of information they now
have access to, but which they have no way to sort or prioritize.
 There's an incredible amount of information available,&quot;
says Robert Griggs, vice president of sales and marketing for
ICONOVEX, &quot;and it's doubling every four years.  Syntactica
can quickly turn that information into useful data that will help
companies make profitable decisions.  Any company that uses digital,
textual data will benefit from incorporating Syntactica into existing
document management systems, databases, etc.&quot;
<P>

 Syntactica breaks text down into phrases using semantic and syntactic
rules to rank the phrases and produce indexes at the level of
detail specified by the user. Syntactica's semantic decisions
are based on an extensive lexicon, or word list.  Specialty lexicons,
such as a legal lexicon, can also be added to enhance the output
when processing technical documents.
<P>
 Through the use of Syntactica, ICONOVEX has introduced Indexicon,
the first automatic indexing software available for WordPerfect
for Windows, Microsoft Word, and Word for Mac.  As a demonstration
of Indexicon, ICONOVEX has produced a hyperlinked version of
the NAFTA agreement, complete with an index generated by Indexicon.
 In only 12 minutes, Indexicon referenced all 1300 pages and turned a
large, unwieldy document into easily accessed reference material.
<P>
 &quot;Now, whatever part of NAFTA effects a specific business,
the user can locate any important facts simply by referring to
their newly generated index,&quot; Griggs adds.
<P>
 The raw output of the Syntactic engine may be integrated with
any software application and format.  Working at a speed of up
to 180 pages per minute, Syntactica can generate back-of-the-book
indexes, concept indexes, indicative abstracts, or all three,
at six different levels of detail.  Syntactica has a broad range
of possible applications including imaging, desktop publishing,
on-line, CD-ROM, and multimedia.
<P>
 Syntactica is the first textual tool built specifically for the
Age of Information.  It solves a problem that was thought to be
unsolvable--teaching the computer to recognize the subtleties
of the English language.  In the process, it provides a way to
turn the textual flood of our age into a reservoir of useful information.
<P>
 The ICONOVEX  Corporation is a software development company and
a wholly-owned subsidiary of INNOVEX, Inc., the world's leading
manufacturer of lead-wire assemblies for the thin film disk drive
market.
<p>
